title: easy beef casserole
directions: Place meat in casserole.
Combine ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
After 20 minutes, stir ingredients.
Cover again and continue cooking until meat is fork-tender.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Fill cookie press with 1/4 dough at a time.
Form desired shapes on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 9 minutes or until set, but not brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, green pepper, 1/2 cup picante sauce and cream cheese over low heat until smooth.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken onto each tortilla; roll up and place seam side down in a lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Stir cheese spread and milk over low heat until smooth.
Pour sauce over tortillas; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Pour remaining picante sauce over enchiladas before serving.

title: crunchy bacon waldorf coleslaw
directions: Mix dressing and sugar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: no no's
directions: Melt bars in double boiler; let cool 5 minutes.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip, mixing evenly.
Drop by teaspoon into crumbs, coating evenly and shaping into round balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Store in plastic bags until ready to use. Makes 150 pieces.
This recipe is great for kids to help make and is a great classroom treat!

title: hilda's caramel apples
directions: Cook to 230° (soft ball stage).
Add vanilla and butter or margarine.
Beat.
Add milk to soften as needed.
Spread on washed, dry apples, to which you have added sticks for handles. Set on waxed paper and cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until center is done.
Cook in loaf pans.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook the green beans lightly.
Add soup, onion rings, water chestnuts, 1/4 cup Velveeta cheese and 1/4 cup grated Cheddar. Mix well and then add 1/4 cup Velveeta and 1/4 cup Cheddar on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soften gelatin in consomme; add softened gelatin to dissolve. Cool.
In bowl, beat cream cheese and mayonnaise; add consomme and other ingredients.
Place in greased molds.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fruit pectin, in a large kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 6 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in fruit pectin; continue boiling for 3 additional minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam with a metal spoon.
Quickly pour jelly into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover at once with metal lids; screw bands tight.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Yields about 3 1/2 cups.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: shrimp-corn soup
directions: Bake corn in slow oven for 1 hour.
Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add diced tomato and cook until blended into onion mixture.
Add roux; stir well.
Add bay leaves and water, stirring after each cup.
When all water is added, boil slowly for 45 minutes.
Add corn; cook 30 more minutes on low heat; stir often.
Add shrimp; cook only until done, about 10 minutes. Turn off heat.
Season with salt, pepper and parsley.
Serve with hot French bread.
Freezes well.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding.
Stir well in all other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.

title: macaroni and cheese variations
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
Stir in one of the following:
1/2 cup sour cream, or 1 cup chopped broccoli and 1 cup chopped ham, or 1 cup cooked peas, 1 cup cooked chicken and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Then bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until heated through.
Or heat in microwave.

title: zesty potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes, leaving skin on, in small chunks.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle dressing mixes over potatoes.
Add water.
Cover with lid.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Spread crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 450° in a shallow baking dish for 10 minutes or until thoroughly warm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° while beginning to make Sweet-Sour Sauce.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring all to a full boil.
Boil for 1 full minute.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 1/4 cups dry oatmeal.
Spoon drop on buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and eat.

title: homemade hot rolls
directions: Mix this well, then pour 3 more cups flour and mix well.
Then let this rise until dough is soft.
Make out roll and let rise until double, then bake at 425° until brown.
Then put rest of dough
in refrigerator until ready to use.
It will keep for a week.

title: lamb in foil
directions: Place lamb chops in a roomy envelope of aluminum foil.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Fold tightly so no steam escapes. Place on baking sheet and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 1.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stirring by hand, add vanilla and nuts. Bake in desired size pan at 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix corn meal and hot water.
Stir well.
Add milk, salt and eggs.
Put in greased skillet or baking dish in a 400° oven.
Bake 45 minutes or until brown.
(I use self-rising corn meal.)

title: summertime punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except limes and lemons, which can be used as a garnish in the punch bowl.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Add seasoning mix and water. Crush 2 handfuls of tortilla chips.
In bowl, mix 1/2 small jar of taco sauce and refried beans.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Soak yeast and water for 10 minutes.
Heat milk until a skin forms on top.
Cool until lukewarm.
Cream oleo, sugar and salt. Add eggs; mix together with milk and yeast then add flour.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Combine pecans and sugar.
Add egg whites and mix until mixture is	completely damp.
Form into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie
sheet.
Press
a	small
hole in center with finger.
Fill
with
preserves.
Put half cherry on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet at once.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Over low heat, simmer 2 cups cider, 6 cloves, allspice and nutmeg for 10 minutes.
Add remaining cider, orange juice, lemonade and brown sugar.
Heat, but do not boil.
Pour in punch bowl and float orange slices pierced with cloves.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In large pot, add soup, peas, carrots, onions, chicken bouillon, diced chicken and 1/2 cup water.
Stir well.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over biscuits, egg noodles, rice or toast.

title: quick breakfast cheesecake
directions: Put biscuits into ungreased pie plate. Mix remaining ingredients, except sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg until smooth and pour over biscuits. Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients.
In small bowl, beat egg slightly; add crushed pineapple and juice, milk and margarine.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture just until moistened.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool bread in pan on rack for 10 minutes, then remove from pan to cool completely.

title: pie shell
directions: Blend with a mixer real slow.
Add 6 Tbsp. ice water and blend by hand till sticks together.
Roll out.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Grease pan or spray with Pam. Sprinkle with nuts and coconut. Mix cake mix according to direction on box. Pour over nuts and coconut. In medium bowl mix 1 pound box powdered sugar, cream cheese, and 2 sticks of butter. Spoon over cake mix. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Cake will not look done, but it is. Cool completely before turning out of pan.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cream cheese to jello mixture and beat until smooth.
Stir in pineapple that has been drained, plus the sugar and vanilla.
Add the 7-Up and stir.

title: drizzle berry pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla (use blender), mixing until well blended.
Blend in 1/2 cup chocolate pieces, melted, and then add egg.

title: date and nut bread(no shortening)
directions: Cut dates in 3 pieces and place in mixing bowl.
Over these, pour water to which soda has been added, stir until dissolved; cook.
Add egg yolk, flour, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Pour in ungreased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese  ball
directions: Grate cheese; chop onions and pecans. Add to cheese. Mix well. Stir in mayonnaise until it begins to form into a ball. Serve with crackers.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix together shredded cabbage and green onion and let sit overnight to blend flavor of two.
Then mix oil and 2 kinds of vinegar (for example--red, wine and Italian) together.
Pour over the cabbage and onion mixture.
Just before serving, mix in dry chow mein noodles.

title: bill's dessert
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and cracker crumbs.
Press into pan, about 8-inch square.
Bake 10 minutes in 325° oven.
Cool.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on oiled griddle or skillet.
Brown on both sides.

title: meat canapes
directions: Saute meat, add onion soup and cheese.
Open crescent rolls and blend pastry together with fingers; add meat mixture and roll like jelly roll.
Baste roll with beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve hot or cold.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Chill milk.
Beat jello and milk.
Add water and lemon juice. Let cool.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add to milk.
Crumble graham crackers.
Mix with melted margarine to form crust.
Add remaining crumbs on top.

title: double apple butter
directions: Soften gelatin in cold lemon juice in blender container for 4 minutes.
Add boiling apple juice and blend on high speed until all gelatin granules are dissolved.
Add salt, undrained apples, cinnamon and vanilla.
Blend until smooth and fluffy.
Fill jars, cover and chill.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields about 3 1/4 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into large shallow dish.
Mix next 3 ingredients in a separate bowl.
Spoon this over the casserole being careful to spread to the edges.
Bake at 400°
for 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and meal; add eggs, melted margarine and vanilla.
Stir all together (do not beat).
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple noodle kugel
directions: Add margarine to hot noodles.
Stir until melted.
Add all ingredients, except crushed cornflakes.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 8 or 9-inch square pans or 1 large oblong pan.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Uncover for crispy top for last 1/2 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cocktail frankfurters
directions: Slice frankfurters into bite size pieces.
Mix mustard and jelly together in a crock-pot.
When heated well and jelly is dissolved with mustard, add frankfurters.
Reduce heat to low. When frankfurters are heated, turn crock-pot off.
Serve by the spoonful with toothpicks to eat them with.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside the flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Blend together shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add flour mixture and mix well, then add raisins, nuts and oatmeal.
This dough is crumbly.
Roll into little balls and put on greased cookie sheet.
Press with a floured fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chew bread
directions: Cream margarine; beat in sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour and vanilla, then fold in chocolate chips.
Place in well-greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and pie filling; add oranges, pineapple and nuts.
Gently fold in whipped topping.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares; serve on lettuce-lined plates, if desired.
Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Put
nonfat
dry
milk
in a large bowl.
Add sugar and cocoa. Stir real well.
Put cocoa mix in clean, dry jars with tightly fitting lids.
Makes hot or cold
chocolate milk.
Use 1/4 cup of cocoa mix for each serving.

title: mexican chalupas
directions: Cook beans according to directions on package.
Shred cheese. Chop onions.
Dice tomatoes.
Shred lettuce.
Pour Fritos in a large bowl.
Serve in this order:
plates, Fritos, cheese, pintos (kept hot in liquid), onions, lettuce, tomatoes and meat sauce. Serve with a light dessert.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add sour milk, cocoa, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in zucchini.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chocolate chips to top of cake before baking, or you can stir the chips into the mixture. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: delicious rice dish
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms for about 20 minutes. Add consomme, water and rice.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes. Serves 6 or more.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Pour in blender and add cream cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Add vanilla, sugar and food coloring.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Add pecans and beat a few seconds.
Pour in 7-Up.
Pour into dish or mold.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in salted water until tender (about 1/2 hour); cut up into bite size pieces.
Add to beaten egg and soups. Add bread cubes; pour into buttered casserole.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Have ready a long sheet of wax paper.
In a large, heavy saucepan, combine the sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil, then add the caramels.
Stir to melt.
When the caramels are melted, boil for 1 minute.
Remove from the heat and stir in the chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Stir in the peanuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: delightfully easy fudge
directions: Heat margarine and peanut butter over medium-low heat until melted.
Stir until blended.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and cocoa.
Stir until completely blended.
Stir in enough sugar to thicken slightly.
Add nuts; stir well.
Add remaining sugar, a little at a time.
Stir well each time.
Mixture will be very thick.
Press into an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: cavatini
directions: Mix all ingredients except Mozzarella cheese. Put in large casserole dish and bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Add Mozzarella cheese last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in water.
In a large bowl, add melted oleo to sugar.
Add beaten egg and dissolved yeast mixture.
Add flour and stir thoroughly to mix.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes or until well browned. Yield: 2 dozen rolls.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix pudding by directions on box.
Spread on cracker crust. Layer bananas, pineapple, Cool Whip, cherries and pecans.
May also serve with Hershey's liquid syrup, dribbled on top.

title: cinnamon tea rolls
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough onto lightly floured wax paper. Press perforations to seal.
Brush with melted butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll, starting at long side.
Cut into 1-inch slices and place in lightly greased miniature muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix powdered sugar and water to make glaze.
Drizzle over rolls while they are still warm.

title: cinnamon raisin biscuits(original recipe)
directions: Sift
and
measure
flour
into
a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Mix
with
3/4 cup milk; knead slightly, and roll into an 8 x 12-inch rectangle.
Melt butter and mix with brown sugar.
Spread
on dough;
sprinkle raisins equally over dough and sprinkle
lightly	with
cinnamon	sugar.	Roll
up
into tubular shape 12 inches long.
With a sharp knife, cut 3/4 to 1-inch portions of tube and place each close to one another on a cookie sheet or baking dish, slightly greased.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: easy make cheesecake
directions: Put in a blender the cream cheese, sour cream and milk.
Blend well.
Pour instant pudding into a bowl.
Add milk mixture.
Stir until it thickens.
Pour mixture into a pie crust.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: lobster tail
directions: Bring to boil.
Put in lobster.
Let boil for 17 minutes.

title: healthy choice crab dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayo, softened cream cheese, and seasonings. Stir in shredded cheese and crabmeat.
Cover and chill for 2 hours. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with fat-free crackers.

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken until browned.
Add soup, onion, thyme, pepper and beans.
Heat to a boil and add to chicken.
Cook until chicken is done.
Add rice and cook until done.

title: don reed's cheesecake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, salt, baking powder and flour.
Mix well and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar together; add 3 egg yolks and 1 egg white to sugar mixture and stir until smooth.
Meanwhile, place 2 cups milk in double boiler and when milk is hot, add the sugar, flour, salt and egg mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
When done, remove from stove; add vanilla and 2 tablespoons peanut butter.

When peanut butter has melted and filling is cool, put in cooked pie crust (plain or graham cracker) and top with meringue, using the whites of eggs saved from the filling or put whipped cream on top.

title: steak diane sauce
directions: Melt butter and slowly add rest of ingredients.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, eggs, bread crumbs, parsley and cheese together. Fry onions in a frying pan.
Make 2 loaves and put side by side in frying pan.
Cook each side of meat loaf until brown.
Add peeled and sliced potatoes, bay leaf and can of tomato sauce.
Cook halfway and add can of peas and juice.
Put lid on and cook until potatoes are done.
Total cooking time:
1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Peel and chop onions.
Chop peppers (remove seed and veins). Butter a baking dish.
Place in it alternate layers of vegetables, beginning and ending with a layer of beans.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and paprika.
Dot each layer with butter.
Cover the dish.
Bake the vegetables in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour or until beans are tender.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until ready to use.
Makes 6 servings.

title: italian pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients into large bowl.
Mix with electric mixer for 20 minutes.
Pour batter into buttered and floured large tube pan.
Put pan in cold oven.
Turn on to 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool and serve.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Brown onion and four tablespoons butter until soft.
Stir in flour and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring continually.
Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce and partially thawed or cooled broccoli. Add eggs; mix gently until well blended.
Put in buttered dish. Cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with remaining two tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into bite size pieces.
Drain thoroughly on towel.
Place in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Chill before serving.
Sprinkle bacon pieces on top.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Divide into thirds and make into 3 balls.
Place 1 ball at a time between 2 sheets of waxed paper and roll dough into oblong shape.
Place 1/3 of date filling on rolled dough; spread out to edges.
Roll up dough and date mixture.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Cut into cookies and bake on greased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Meat butter in saucepan.
Saute onion in hot butter for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes, hot water, salt and pepper and cook for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add evaporated milk.
Heat and garnish with chopped parsley.

title: mommy's dressing
directions: Boil all ingredients until chicken is done.
Remove bay leaves and chicken.
Debone chicken.
Disgard bones, fat and skin.
Set meat aside.

title: "aussie lamingtons"
directions: Bake cake as directions on packet instruct, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch ovenproof baking dish.
Cool, then cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: cheese roasted vegetables
directions: Place potatoes and carrots (cut up) in greased 13 x 9 baking dish.
Drizzle with oil; add basil, oregano, salt and pepper. Toss lightly to coat.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Add zucchini, bell pepper and garlic.
Stir; return to oven.
Bake 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese; return to oven 3 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Combine soup, chilies, onions and some green tops, sour cream, olives and half of the cheeses; set aside 2 cups of this mixture. Add chicken to remaining mixture.
Place about 4 tablespoons of mixture at end of each tortilla and roll up.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan (about 8 per pan).
Place some of the mixture without chicken over the top.
Sprinkle remaining cheeses over top, then green onion tops and sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate overnight, a must!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab salad
directions: In 8-inch square pan spread softened cream cheese to cover the bottom.
On top of the cream cheese, spread the crab meat.
Spread salsa on top of the crab and chill.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In a mixing bowl, combine beaten eggs, sugar, melted chocolate, cooking oil, baking powder and vanilla. Gradually add flour to chocolate mixture, stirring until thoroughly combined. Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours or until easy to handle. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Roll balls in powdered sugar to coat generously. Place 1-inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are set and tops are crackled. Cool cookies on a wire rack. If desired, sprinkle with additional powdered sugar. Makes about 48.

title: sue's chocolate pie
directions: Add all ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick. Cool and pour in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: ham-potato bake
directions: Layer 1/2 the potatoes and 1/2 the carrots in a 2 quart casserole.
Stir together soup, 1/2 cheese, milk, instant, salt and pepper and ham.
Pour 1/2 over potatoes and carrots.
Repeat layers.

title: spiced cider warm-up
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients in a saucepan for 10 minutes. Strain.
Serve hot with fruit slices and cinnamon stick for garnish.

title: chile cheesers
directions: Mix everything together and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray (e.g.
Pam).
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cut into small squares when slightly cooled.
Can be served hot or cold.
Can be chilled and reheated.
If using glass pan, reduce heat by 25°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Make pudding and jello according to package directions.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes, then peel.
Combine all ingredients together and mash.
Pour into two 9-inch baking shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Add soup to melted butter, salt, pepper, onion, 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese and sour cream in saucepan.
Heat and stir briefly. Put frozen hash browns in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour contents in saucepan over potatoes.
Mix until all blended.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: tofu spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in wok or large heavy pot.
Add garlic and onions; saute for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, green peppers and mushrooms; saute for 3 to 4 minutes more.
Add water.
Drop in 1 bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Cover pot and simmer for 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for about 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves and serve over spaghetti noodles.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: taco pizza dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature. Two tablespoons of instant onions can be substituted for real onions (I use them). Combine and spread the mixture on a glass round plate. Let this set overnight.

title: potato or macaroni salad dressing
directions: Mix together; put on your salad!

title: mattie spain's blueberry casserole
directions: Mix
together
and
press into (clear) glass casserole. Bake at
325° about 25 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Cool.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken; cut into pieces.
Lightly grease bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken in dish.
Combine soup and sour cream; pour over top of chicken.
Combine margarine, crackers and poppy seed; pour over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: 3 step cheesecake recipe
directions: Cream cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well. Pour batter into graham cracker pie crust (no spring-form pan needed).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool for 3 hours.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: iris' breakfast dish
directions: Note:
Bacon, ham or another meat may be substituted for sausage.

title: chicken and noodles parmesan
directions: in a saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook mushrooms and carrots until tender and liquid is evaporated.
Stir in half and half, remaining butter, peas and nutmeg.
Heat to simmering. Gradually stir in cheese. Add chicken.
Heat thoroughly.
Cook noodles and drain.
Toss hot noodles with chicken mixture.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish. Lay raw bacon strips on top of beans.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mexican delight
directions: Brown meat and drain. Stir in the chiles and simmer 10 minutes. Layer Doritos chips on top of meat mixture. Layer American cheese slices on top of Doritos and let cheese melt. If any meat mixture is left, remove cheese and Doritos. Add fresh chips and cheese. May be frozen or refrigerated.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Stir together until smooth 1 tablespoon cornstarch with vinegar, catsup and soy sauce.
Stir in sugar and pineapple syrup until sugar is dissolved; set aside.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt margarine in a small square cake pan in the oven.
Dip biscuits in melted butter.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together in a bowl.
Dip buttered biscuits in cinnamon and sugar mixture, then place biscuits back into buttered square pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients
except bread crumbs.
Make patties then roll in bread crumbs
and
fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, onions, grated cheese and taco seasoning. Spread on tortilla.
Roll up; slice into 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Dip into favorite salsa while eating.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Flatten slightly with bottom of a glass dipped in powdered sugar.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until light brown.
Roll in additional powdered sugar while warm. Sprinkle with more sugar after cooled.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in water.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, soda/water mixture and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Make 2 rolls, wrap each in wax paper, place in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, slice 1/8-inch thick, bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in pan. Brown and drain. Add macaroni, Ragu and sugar. Put in glass dish. Break cheese slices in half from corner to corner. Lay around edge. Melt cheese and serve.

title: beef brisket
directions: Braise brisket on all sides.
Add sliced onion and garlic. Cover top with garlic salt, pepper and paprika to taste.
Cover pan and cook on moderate flame for 1 hour.
Remove meat from pot, leaving vegetables.
Slice the meat thin and return to pot.
Cover and cook on low heat for about 1 hour until done.
Add small amount of water, if necessary, and turn pieces frequently.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bone.
Cook egg noodles and chopped onion in broth.
Drain off most of broth.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread into one large or two small casserole dish(es).
Cover with bread crumbs and melted butter. (Great to freeze and cook later.)
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: confetti pasta salad
directions: Mix all but cheese and chill.
Add cheese; toss and serve. Serves 6.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Grate cabbage, mango and carrots.
Sprinkle salt over and let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out liquid and drain.
Boil together sugar, water, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed and set aside to cool.
Pour over cabbage mix and pack into containers and freeze. Will keep for a year.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Add frozen orange juice. Add pineapple juice, sugar and crushed pineapple.
Mash bananas and then add to mixture.
Mix all ingredients well.
About 30 minutes before serving, add sherbet.
Serves about 50 people.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup, melted butter and pecans.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: chewy date torte
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, beating until thoroughly combined.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir into mixing bowl.
Add milk, butter and vanilla; stir just until combined.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until the pudding tests done.
Cool.
Cut into squares; top with whipped cream and additional nuts, if desired.
Yield:
9 servings.

title: wassail
directions: Mix everything together except orange juice.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add orange juice.
Heat until hot and serve.
Take out cinnamon sticks and cloves.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Place bread dough in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Thaw (can be placed in refrigerator overnight).
When thawed, spread dough in pan.
Spread with pie filling.
In bowl, mix butter, flour and sugar until crumbly.
Sprinkle over filling. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease a square baking pan or dish.
Combine eggs, milk and butter.
Mix well.
Add the corn bread mix and cream-style corn. Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creole chicken
directions: Prepare chicken as for frying.
Place in skillet with plenty of shortening.
Fry fast, until a nice brown.
Drain off all grease.
Add tomatoes, green pepper and celery.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Cover tightly.
Let cook about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: mardon's pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and sprinkle with garlic salt. Chill.
(You can add or omit variety and amounts to personal preference.)

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients in a pot on the stove until well mixed and heated.
Serve in a crock-pot (low heat) with scoop size Fritos.

title: beef stew with potato dumplings
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge meat in flour mixture. Cook meat and onions in bacon drippings until onions are tender and meat is browned.
Stir in broth, water, vinegar and carrots. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4 inch thick.
Season with salt and pepper. Coat with cornmeal.
Add tomato slices to heated bacon drippings in skillet.
Fry slowly, turning once.

title: quick-as-a-mix fruit cake
directions: Put nuts, dates and cherries in a large mixing bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt over nuts and fruit.
Mix with hands until nuts and fruit are coated with flour mixture. Beat eggs until foamy.
Add vanilla; stir into nut and fruit mixture.
Turn into well-greased bread pan.
Spread and pack down. Bake in a 300° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: mexican cornbread salad
directions: Mix cornbread and bake as directed.
Crumble cooled cornbread in bottom of salad bowl.
Layer all ingredients in order given. Spread Miracle Whip all over top.
Cover well and refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together all ingredients, except pecan halves, and put in pie shell.
Place pecans around top of pie.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together; let stand a day or more.

title: ten layer chocolate cake
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs; mix well. Add flour alternately with milk. Mix well.
Add vanilla. Grease and flour 8 1/2-inch cake pans. Spread 1/2 cup batter in each pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: grandma grabill's popsicles
directions: Blend all together in blender and pour into popsicle molds and freeze.
I do not usually measure, so I'm guessing.
I just put whatever I have around in and it always comes out different. Grandkid's favorite!

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain. While spaghetti is hot, mix with butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs. Spread spaghetti in buttered 10-inch pie plate.
In skillet cook ground beef and sausage with casing removed; drain grease.
Add onion and green pepper to meat mixture during last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Chop tomatoes; add tomatoes and their liquid, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and crushed garlic to meat mixture.
Cook until heated throughout and bubbly.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
Spoon meat mixture on top of cottage cheese. Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese in center of pie.
Bake 5 minutes or until melted.
Remove from oven.
Let stand at room temperature for 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dip for fruits
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fruit.
Place in bowl in refrigerator for up to 2 hours to solidify.
Place bowl in center of tray; surround with fruits.
Fun for summer.
Enjoy!

title: anita's paper sack apple pie
directions: Pare apples, cut into small slices, 1/8 inch thick.
Mix flour, sugar and nutmeg together.
Toss apple slices into this mixture until well coated.
Pour into pie shell.
Place the pie in a large paper sack.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake at 400 degrees for one hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Place cream cheese in a blender or processor and mix well.
Add sugar, mayonnaise, cranberry sauce, pecans and pineapple; blend. Put in a bowl and top with cool whip and chill.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough dressing as needed.
Only use dill pickles (sweet are Yucky).
Put on bread, wrap in foil. Put in oven at 350 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dilled oyster crackers
directions: Place last 5 ingredients in large leakproof bowl.
Add crackers.
Give 5 shakes every 10 minutes for an hour.

title: hobo's dinner(serves 1 to 2)
directions: You will need 1 (12 x 15-inch) piece of tinfoil.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Remove meat from bones and chop. Brown rice in shortening until golden.
Set aside.
Brown vegetables, chicken, chili powder, Tabasco, tomatoes and chicken broth.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven until rice is done and liquid is absorbed.
Add more water if needed.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Place flour in a bowl.
Beat eggs and milk in another bowl. Place bread crumbs in another bowl.
Roll balls first in flour mixture, then in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Now they are ready for deep frying.
Place meat balls in wire basket for deep frying.
Fry a few at a time, covering bottom of wire basket.
Pour cooking oil in fryer at depth of 2 inches.
Heat to 375°, then lower the basket containing sauerkraut balls in the hot oil and cook until golden brown; remove to dry on paper towel.

title: apple dressing
directions: Blend together applesauce, sour cream and salad dressing. Add celery seed. Chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place olive oil into frying pan and heat through.
Add chicken and stir-fry just until browned.
Set aside.
Mix milk and soup. Crumble 1 can of the onion rings into the mixture.
Add the cooked chicken and mix well.
Place the green beans into baking dish. Pour the mixture over the beans.
Place the remaining can of onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lazy fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add lemon juice.
Dip chicken in mixture.
Roll in mixture of dry ingredients and place on cookie sheet or cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: plum compote
directions: Weigh the plums after pitting.
Mix everything together and boil to a jelly consistency.

title: chicken, bacon and cheddar sandwiches
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.

Remove bacon and drain on paper towels. Reserve 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet. Cook chicken in hot drippings 6 to 8 minutes or until no longer pink and juices run clear, turning once. Spread mayonnaise and Dijon on cut sides of rolls.
Top bottom half of each roll with cooked chicken breast half, 1 slice cheese, 1 slice cooked bacon, 1 tomato slice and 1 lettuce leaf. Cover each with top half of roll.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: In a large glass dish, 9 x 13, prepare the jello according to package (except use 2 cups hot and 1 cup cold water). Add drained oranges. Add pineapple. Mix well and refrigerate. Cover with foil until firm. Arrange marshmallows in a single layer. Put a thin layer of Cool Whip on top of marshmallows; cut in squares.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix oil, eggs and brown sugar.
Mix dry ingredients.
Pour egg mixture over flour mixture.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: makashick
directions: Brown ground beef and onions and drain.
Place in bottom of a 2 1/2 quart Pyrex dish.
Pour corn on top of beef.
Place mashed potatoes on top layer.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: yuletide appetizer
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Spread on Melba rounds and bake on baking stone or baking sheet for 5 to 10 minutes.
Chop green and red peppers finely and sprinkle on each round.
Serve.

title: ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil noodles; drain and put in oblong baking dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over noodles and stir. Break up ham and stir into noodle mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
(You can add more cheese, if desired.)
Dot with butter. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it comes to a boil. Boil 4 minutes. Remove from heat. Add chips and creme. Beat until chips are melted and mixture begins to thicken. Mix in vanilla and walnuts. Pour into buttered 9x13 pan. Cool and cut into squares. Makes about 3 pounds.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Beat the ingredients with a spoon.
Add just enough snow until consistency of ice cream.

title: cheese smackles
directions: Cream margarine; mix with grated cheese.
Sift pepper and salt with flour.
Gradually add flour mixture to margarine.
Add Rice Krispies crushed slightly.
Make small balls.
Place on a baking sheet.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 60.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: key lime pie(low fat - sugar free)
directions: Add yogurt and cool whip to jell-o. Pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: green beans caesar(delicious!)
directions: Cook string beans.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Toss beans with oil, vinegar, onion, garlic and pepper.
Pour in an ungreased 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over beans.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Nice for company!
Enjoy.

title: macaroni and meat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake 1 hour or until cheese melts.

title: bread or dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast, water and sugar in small bowl.
Put 1 cup of flour and the salt in a large bowl.
Add oil, milk, egg and yeast mixture.
Blend until moistened.
Beat with electric mixer 3 minutes at low speed.
Stir in by hand 1 1/2 to 2 cups of flour (enough to make batter stiff).
Cover; let rise until double.
Push down; shape into round loaf.
Place on cookie sheet; let rise 30 minutes.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chow mein haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in microwave. This takes about 2 minutes. Stir twice.
Add chow mein noodles and cashews to melted butterscotch morsels.
Drop in clusters on wax paper.
Let sit to harden.

title: brownies
directions: Grease cookie pan with sides.
Cream well sugar and Crisco. Then add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each and chocolate. Sift together flour and salt.
Mix well, then add vanilla and nuts.
Blend and spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cocktail nibbles
directions: Start oven at
Mix pretzel sticks (broken smaller) with
peanuts
and	cereal.
In
large roasting pan, heat butter until melted and stir in Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion and celery salt.
Mix well and pour over cereal mixture; mix
well. Cover
and	bake 1 hour.
Remove cover;
stir well and bake 1 hour more.
Stir occasionally.
This makes 4 quarts of flavorful nibbles.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour; add hot water.
Cool slightly. Roll between wax paper.
Makes 4 crusts or 2 double crust pies. Freezes real well.

title: spaghetti in pasta broccoli
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Also cook broccoli until tender and drain. Melt cheese with milk.
Place spaghetti in 9 x 13-inch pan; place broccoli on top of spaghetti.
Put diced ham on top of broccoli, then pour cheese on top of all of it.
Place in oven until warm all the way through.
Serve while hot.

title: egg's annapolis
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter and saute onion.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Slowly stir in milk and cook 5 minutes until thick.
Add crab, sherry and cheese, stirring to combine.
Split and toast English muffins.
Poach eggs.
Arrange eggs on muffins and cover with crab sauce.
Sprinkle with bacon and serve.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, shortening and salt; let cool. Add 1 cup tepid water to yeast and dissolve; then sift in flour. Mix other ingredients well and knead well.
Place in refrigerator for 8 hours before using.
Make into rolls and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 450°.
Dough is good for 2 or 3 weeks.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown beef and onion, drain.
Add Prego sauce.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Boil manicotti noodles in salted water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add noodles carefully so as not to break; drain gently.
After noodles cool, fill with cheese mixture (egg, cottage cheese and Parmesan).
In baking dish, pour thin layer of sauce.
Arrange filled noodles over sauce.
Make sure noodles do not touch.
Pour remaining sauce over noodles.
Top with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and chill until set.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Mix all with mayonnaise until moist.
Put in casserole.
Top with 1 1/2 cups potato chips and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Break the pretzels; add melted butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: baked rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked maple bananas
directions: Place butter in
shallow microproof baking dish.
Place in oven.
Cook High
minute.
At
pause,
add
maple syrup, blend well.
Add bananas and spoon mixture over bananas.
Cook High for 1 minute.
At pause,
turn bananas and cook for 1 1/2 minutes more on High.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and cinnamon. Serve warm.

title: microwave spinach and noodles parmesan
directions: To microwave:
Place onion in 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with lid; microwave on High 3 minutes or until tender, stirring once during cooking.
Add spinach.
Cover; microwave on High 5 minutes or until spinach is thawed, stirring twice during cooking.
Stir in soup, sour cream, cheese and spices.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Follow cake box directions and bake.
As soon as cake is done, take out of oven and poke holes all over cake.
Then pour condensed milk over cake.
Make sure you cover the whole cake. Then pour caramel topping over the condensed milk.
Cover cake and refrigerate until cool.
Before serving, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle crushed Heath bars and nuts.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Add apples and flour.
Mix together and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes (325° in glass) in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or a Bundt pan.
Can be served warm or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In large bowl mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in water and margarine.
Mix in only enough reserved flour to make a soft dough.
On floured surface knead 4 minutes.
On greased baking sheet, roll dough to 10 x 14-inches.
Spread dressing down center third of dough length. Top with layers of beef, cheese and sauerkraut.
Make cuts from filling to dough edges at 1-inch intervals along sides of filling. Alternate sides, folding strips at an angle across filling.
Let raise 15 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Rinse crab and drain well.
Flake or tear apart.
Mix cheese, crab and juice.
Cover with cocktail sauce.
(Make sure it's Hoffman's - will make a difference in the taste.)
Best if refrigerated for 2 to 4 hours.

title: sweet corn muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until soft and combined.
Break the eggs into the butter and sugar; beat together with a large spoon. Beat well.
Add the corn meal, then sift in the flour alternately with the milk, beating after each addition, until all ingredients are combined.
Divide into 12 greased muffin pan sections.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: tuna and cheese noodles
directions: Mix all in casserole dish.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift and measure the flour.
Resift with the soda and salt. Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk, and mashed bananas to creamed mixture.
Add flour mixture, beat thoroughly.
Pour into well greased loaf pan and bake for one and a half hours at 350 degrees.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Boil the hen until tender, take meat off the bones and save the broth.
Place remaining ingredients in a large pan or dish and mix.
Place the chicken on mixture and cover with broth.
Add hot water, if needed.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mississippi mud(cookie or cake)
directions: Mix everything but the marshmallows together and pour into a 17 x 11-inch greased and floured baking pan. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Take cake out and turn oven to 350°. Put marshmallows over cake and put back into oven until the marshmallows are puffy and brown, 7 to 10 minutes.

title: spinach-cheese pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Cook spinach according to directions.
Drain and press out liquid.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat oil and gently cook onions until wilted.
Stir spinach and onions into eggs with ham, cheese, Ricotta cheese, salt and pepper. Line a 10-inch pie plate with half the pastry.
Add spinach mixture.
Cover with remaining pastry.
Cut 6 (1-inch) vents in it. Seal and flute the ends.
Bake in preheated 425° oven (on the rack below center) until golden, 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add the juices of the blueberries and pineapple to make 1 cup.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Let congeal in 2-quart dish.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well.
Turn into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and keep refrigerated.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except buttered crumbs.
Reserve stuffing mix crumbs for topping.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter before adding to other ingredients.
Dilute soup with 1/3 cup milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese; add sugar. Beat egg yolk. Add flour and vanilla. Chill 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls. Put on greased cookie sheet. Press pecan into cookie. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together and add Tang and pudding.
Mix well and chill.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; save broth.
Cool chicken; cut up and put in baking dish.
Mix soup and broth; pour over chicken.
Mix flour with margarine until crumbly; add milk.
Pour over chicken and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: blueberry jam
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Boil jars and tops before filling. Seal.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix diced chicken, celery and lemon juice together; chill. Mix together rest of ingredients; stir into preceding mixture. Chill before serving.

title: polynesian spareribs
directions: Step #1:
Simmer ribs for about 1 hour until tender, but not falling apart. Drain liquid.

title: norwegian christmas cake
directions: Grease bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat eggs and 1 cup sugar until light and foamy (5 to 7 minutes).
Stir in 1 tablespoon water.
Add flour, cornstarch and baking powder.
Stir until blended.
Pour in pan; bake 35 to 45 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack 5 minutes.
Remove cake from pan.
While cake is warm, cut cake horizontally into 2 layers. Place layers, cut side up on rack.
In cup, stir instant coffee plus 1/4 cup warm water until coffee dissolves.
Drizzle coffee mixture over 1 cake layer; drizzle orange juice concentrate over the other cake layer. Cool completely.

title: quick rolls
directions: Sift 3 cups flour with baking powder, sugar, salt and soda. Cut in the shortening. Dissolve yeast in the water and add enough sour milk to make 1 cup of liquid. Add to the dry ingredients. Stir in additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on board and knead for 1 minute.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in pan and let rise 1 hour.
Bake about 15 minutes at 425°.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook bouillon cubes in 1 quart water with celery and onions. Add potatoes, vegetables and 2nd quart water.
Cook 30 minutes. Add soup and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble into soup.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco well.
Add eggs and flour alternately. Add other ingredients, stirring in pineapple well.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 90 minutes.
Use a Bundt pan.

title: fudge sauce
directions: In a double-boiler, melt butter and chocolate very slowly. Add sugar and salt until dissolved.
Stir in milk, slowly.
Makes 1 quart.
Serve warm over cake and ice cream.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add uncooked oatmeal, alternating with milk.
Sift together flour, salt and cinnamon.
Blend into oatmeal mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: skillet apple slices
directions: Select one beautiful bundle of joy.
Choose weight and color to accommodate family preference.
Choose one self-rising flour so you'll never have to worry about weight or height.
Sprinkle generously with affection and pat dry (constantly in the beginning).
Marinate in love for the next few years, adding a new ingredient when appropriate.
Never pour into a mold.
Your cookies need plenty of room to expand.

title: roast goose
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place goose, breast side up, on rack, about 1-inch from bottom of roaster.
After 30 minutes, turn down to 375° and prick goose with fork around breast, back and drumsticks, letting excess fat escape.
Let cook about 20 minutes per pound.

title: zesty barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 5 to 10 minutes. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups.

title: onion and bacon quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large frying pan, cook onions in butter over medium heat.
Stir occasionally until onions are soft and begin to brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: irish italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain fat.
Add other ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer for 45 minutes.
Cook spaghetti and mix together.
Great with Parmesan cheese.

title: spinach madeleine in chafing dish
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Set spinach aside.

title: canadian bacon potato skins(low calorie)
directions: Place potatoes in microwave safe plate.
Prick with fork. Microwave until tender 18-22 minutes, turning once.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp leaving 1/4 inch shell.
Save pulp for another use.
Combine oil and hot pepper sauce.
Brush over potato shells.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Cut each shell in half lengthwise.
Place on baking sheet coated with non-stick spray.
Sprinkle bacon, tomato, onion and cheese.
Bake 450 degrees 12-14 minutes or until heated and cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream.
Makes 8 Servings - 4 points.

title: four fruit shake
directions: Combine orange juice, milk, strawberries (washed and hulled), pineapple, banana and coconut extract in container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Pour into glasses and serve immediately.

title: bryon's diabetic popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O , Kool-Aid and sugar substitute in hot water. Add cold water now.
If you don't have popsicle trays, you can use ice trays.
Fill trays, cover with Saran Wrap over top and place toothpick into Kool-Aid for sticks.

title: great pork steak
directions: Put flour in one flat bowl.
Mix eggs and 1 tablespoon water in another.
Mix bread crumbs and seasoning in a third.
Dip each piece of meat into flour, then egg, then crumb mixture.
Brown coated meat in oil and top with onion slices.
Add remaining water (if needed).
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until done.

title: bread and butter squash
directions: Bring to boil; add squash.
Bring to boil again.
Boil only 2 minutes.
Pack into jars, fill with liquid and seal.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Mix dry ingredients and mix with creamed mixture.
Add oats, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: life giving vitamins
directions: Don't fail to use daily these vitamins so necessary to beauty and health.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into mixture, mixing well.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a glass baking dish, 11 x 7-inches. In medium size saucepan, combine peaches, 1/2 cup of the sugar and water.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Keep mixture hot.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Rub mixture over chicken 30 minutes before grilling.
Grill chicken for 10 minutes.
Turn and cook for another 15 to 25 minutes.
Pierce chicken with a fork.
When the juices run yellow, the chicken is done.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados; mix in everything else.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons mayonnaise.

title: party punch
directions: Combine gelatin and sugar. Add boiling water and stir until dissolved. Stir in cold water and juices. Chill.

title: corn fritters
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat well.
Drop corn batter into hot oil by tablespoons.
Fry 4 minutes until golden brown.
Serve hot with syrup or plain as vegetable with chicken.

title: baked bean hot dish
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake to heat through.

title: kolacky cookies
directions: Sift the flour.
Add baking powder.
Set aside.
Cream the butter or margarine, cream cheese, milk and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolk.
Add flour mixture.
Knead until smooth dough.
Chill dough.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix and bake ingredients at 350°.

title: green beans
directions: Cut bacon in 1-inch slices.
Place in boiler or frying pan. Cook slow until brown; add diced onion.
Saute until onion is tender.
Drain 1 can of beans.
Add to onion and bacon.
Add the other can including liquid.
Cook on low heat for a few minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and put into casserole dish.
Cover with soup.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious green beans
directions: Combine green beans and artichoke hearts in a bowl.
Pour salad dressing over top; toss.
Chill at least 2 hours; drain. Spoon green bean mixture into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry-orange nut bread
directions: Blend flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice and peel, ending with dry ingredients.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Divide batter evenly between 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This freezes well.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat ingredients together, put into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Make paste of food coloring and cocoa and stir in.
Add milk alternately with sifted flour.
Add vanilla.
Add soda to vinegar in separate bowl, then add soda/vinegar mixture to cake and blend.
Do not beat. Pour in well-greased, lightly floured 8-inch pans (3).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Red Velvet Frosting.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and milk. Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip. Layer cake, cheese filling and pie filling in glass serving dish. Chill.

title: turtles
directions: Cook to boiling the syrup and Eagle Brand milk, stirring constantly for 15 minutes.
Drop by tablespoons onto pecan halves on buttered wax paper.
Freeze until ready to dip (2 hours).
Dip in chocolate (almond bark works well).

title: mints
directions: Combine sugar, butter, water and flavoring.
Cream with mixer or by hand.
It can be put in cookie press or rolled and cut.
If put in press, I use 1/3 cup water.

title: honey mustard pork chops
directions: You will also need 1 Reynolds large oven bag.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in oven bag.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add orange juice, honey and mustard to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Sprinkle pork chops with basil and seasoned salt; place in bag.
Place carrot and apple slices in bag around pork chops.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Bake until pork chops are tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand in bag 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey turnovers
directions: Prepare your favorite pastry or a packaged mix for a 9-inch single crust.
Evenly brush entire surface with butter.
Set aside.

title: rhubarb
directions: Cut rhubarb into 3/4-inch pieces (approximately 3 cups).
Heat oven to 300°.
Pour boiling water over rhubarb.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain water.
Spoon rhubarb into baking dish.
Spoon sugar over rhubarb and bake 15 minutes.
Stir and bake 15 more minutes.

title: quick cheese cake
directions: Beat all ingredients and place in pie shell.
Chill.
May be served with your favorite fruit topping, cherries, strawberries, blackberries, etc.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Shake well or blend in blender.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Drain.
Mash into large chunks of potatoes. Mix milk and sour cream.
Pour and mix into potatoes.
Add grated cheese.
Cover top of potatoes with cheese and chives.
This all goes into a casserole dish that's been greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Arrange asparagus flat on a large plate.
Grate boiled eggs and spread on top of asparagus.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Spread a thin layer of mayonnaise on top of this.
Last, spread a layer of stuffed olives on top.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: layered turkey salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Set aside. Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and white pepper.
Spread over salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and cover cookie sheet.
Bake and cool. Mix mayonnaise and dressing mix; spread on cool crust.
Cut vegetables into small bite-size pieces and cover cream cheese mixture.
Let stand 4 to 6 hours.

title: baked curry chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Then, mix together all other ingredients; spread evenly over chicken.
Cover with foil and continue baking 30 to 40 minutes more or until chicken is tender.
Serves 4.

title: layered salad
directions: Break lettuce into pieces and layer with rest of ingredients in the order listed.
Place in refrigerator to mellow overnight (covered).
Toss when ready to serve.

title: macaroni chili mix up
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Add all other ingredients; blend well.
Simmer until onion and pepper are done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cheddar, onion, green pepper, pimentos, lemon juice, salt and Tabasco.
Roll in ball; refrigerate 30 minutes.
Take out of refrigerator.
Roll in pecans.

title: lemon pecan cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter.
Add brown sugar and sugar and cream well.
Combine egg, vanilla and milk and beat until smooth.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt and add to the mixture.
When beaten smooth, add oats or wheat flakes.
Beat the mixture well.
Drop cookies 2 inches apart on a well-greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.
Makes 3 dozen.
Can add any optional ingredients, if desired.

title: poke cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in 24 paper lined muffin cups.
Remove from oven.
Poke a hole down through the center of each cupcake with a plastic drinking straw (larger holes can be made around the center hole).
After holes are made, pour milk into shaker cup; add pudding mix and powdered sugar. Cover and shake vigorously 1 minute.
Before pudding thickens, pour pudding into holes. Allow remaining pudding to thicken; then spoon over top of each cupcake, swirling it to frost the cupcake. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: roasted red potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes (do not peel), one or two per person.

In a 9 x 13-inch roasting pan, add the oil and garlic and toss to coat potatoes. Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake, uncovered, for about 40 to 50 minutes, turning potatoes once or twice to brown. When done, dot with butter.

title: easter cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a cheesecloth bag. Press in between two boards for about 1 hour.
Then slice and serve.

title: aunt cathie's apple pie
directions: Mix together; pour into pie plate.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in bowl.
Add; mix well.
Add next 4 ingredients; mix gently.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm, garnished with whipped cream.

title: guacamole dip
directions: A food processor works best, but a blender and hand mixer both substitute (for hand mixing be sure to cut everything fine).
Beat all ingredients except tomato until creamy; stir in tomato.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand until well blended.
Pinch off small balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients & beat until smooth.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: coconut slush
directions: Freeze.
Put desired amount in glass and add 7-Up to fill glass.

title: nanna's chicken special
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to your taste.
Place in baking dish and cover; cook until done, 40 to 45 minutes.
Drain liquid in medium bowl and add cream of chicken soup and blend well.
Pour over chicken evenly.
Put biscuits on top of chicken and soup. Cook until done, but not brown.
Put grated cheese over biscuits and bake until cheese is melted.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook meat and onion in a large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in the tomatoes, uncooked rice, water, Worcestershire sauce, Italian seasoning and pepper. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 18 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: rodger's favorite scrambled egg medley(serves 10 to 14.)
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add milk and parsley.
Scramble but leave moist.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with sour cream; spread over eggs.
Cook bacon until crisp; crumble and spread over sour cream layer.
Grate cheese and mix together.
Saute mushrooms; place on top of cheeses.
Add thinly sliced tomatoes.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.
May be prepared ahead and refrigerated or frozen (add 10 to 15 minutes to baking time).

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix well.
Form into 6 cakes.
Fry in butter or oil 5 minutes on each side.

title: pizzelle
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar gradually.
Add oil; beat until well blended.
Add extracts and vanilla.
Add flour and salt a little at a time.
Chill dough 2 hours, overnight or several days to enrich flavor.
Pour batter on pizzelle iron.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until done.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: layered pea salad
directions: In large glass bowl, layer with lettuce in bottom, then onions, celery and peas on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Cover with remaining ingredients and stir well. Really cold, crisp summer salad.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream crisco and brown sugar, beat in eggs and molasses. Sift together flour, soda, ginger and salt.
Add to cream mixture, add boiling water gradually and beat well.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, chopped olives, green chiles and picante sauce.
Fill tortillas and roll. Chill well. After they are well chilled, cut rolls into slices.
May also serve as follows: Spread mixture on 1 tortilla.
Put a second tortilla on top, making mixture in the middle. Chill well and cut into quesadilla-like wedges.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix together potatoes, cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fry bacon until crisp and crumble over top of potato mixture. Slice olives and put over bacon.
Bake at 350° until heated through (approximately 30 minutes).

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in beaten eggs and brown sugar.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients and then add chocolate chips and nuts. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until done when tested.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup and Cheddar.
Place in greased casserole dish. Top with onions and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle additional grated cheese on top and broil until golden and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until it makes a long thread, then add the raw peanuts and vanilla and cook until it turns a light brown and you can hear peanuts crackling.
It will be very stiff.
Add soda; stir well and pour onto buttered pans.
Will not hurt to stir after peanuts are added.

title: sausage roll
directions: Spread bread dough flat on cookie sheet.
Brown sausage and crumble on top of bread dough.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Roll up as you would like a jelly roll.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: venison(deer meat)
directions: In iron pot, put meat, onion, garlic, bell pepper, salt, Season-All and oil together.
Cover with water; bring to a boil then reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer for approximately 2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Turn heat up to high and let remaining water cook out of meat; then stir meat and brown without letting meat scorch. Add a little water until desired thickness.
Makes a thick gravy. Add cream of mushroom soup, if desired.

title: delicious bean soup
directions: Cook until beans are tender.
Then add 1 can stewed tomatoes. Cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve with corn bread.

title: the best chili yet
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Best cooked the day before using.

title: anise drop cookies
directions: Beat eggs for 5 1/2 minutes in a large bowl.
Add sugar gradually, then add flavoring.
When all sugar has been added, continue beating for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add flour and baking powder. Beat 5 minutes more.

title: june epperson's cookies
directions: In mixer, whip the oleo until soft and fluffy. Add the brown sugar and mix well. Add the eggs and mix well, then add the flour. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked squash
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain.
Saute onion in margarine. Mash squash; add onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Add milk and part of crumbled crackers.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly blend cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Fold in pineapple, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Refrigerate several hours.
Shape into ball; roll in nuts.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough and arrange on bottom of 15 x 10-inch baking dish.
Press dough evenly into pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Spread over cooled cookie crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese (pineapple, banana, kiwi, strawberries and grapes, but in half).
Combine orange marmalade and water, stirring to mix.
Spoon over fruit.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: frosted chews
directions: Place sugar and corn syrup in medium size pan. Stir to combine. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add Special K. Stir until evenly coated.
Press mixture evenly and firmly in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cool.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels together in top of double boiler over hot, but not boiling, water or in small saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Spread evenly over Special K cereal mixture.
Let stand in cool place until firm.
Cut into bars to serve.
Yields 4 dozen frosted chews, 2 x 1-inch.

title: pecan pie, not so sweet, a la june veneable
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and margarine. Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Pour mixture over pastry. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
The nuts will rise to the top and form a crusted layer.

title: cajun cake
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together into a bowl.
Add pineapple with juice and eggs.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes in oblong greased pan.

title: goo-ey cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, press on bottom of pan, then beat cream cheese, the 2 eggs and powdered sugar, pour over cake mix and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine lettuce, ground beef and cheese.
Pour salad dressing mixture over all.

title: inmate jack mackerel spread
directions: Mix everything together except for crackers or bread. Spread over crackers or bread. This is like tuna salad.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix everything together in a large saucepan.
Put on high until it boils, then simmer until thickens.
Stir occasionally.

title: lemon-blueberry pudding cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light.
Add egg yolks; beat well. Add flour, salt and lemon juice and beat well.
Gently mix in berries and milk.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This is better the second or third day.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix vanilla and tapioca pudding in the pineapple and mandarin juice (3 cups).
Cook pudding in the juice until slightly thickened. Pour pudding mixture over fruit and mix well.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup to a hard boil.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatine and cream cheese.
Beat until completely blended.
Stir in shrimp, celery and onions.
Gently fold in mayo.
Refrigerate 8 to 10 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: skillet maple apples
directions: In 10-inch skillet melt butter.
Stir in sugar and cornstarch. Stir in remaining ingredients except apples.
Cover over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened (6 to 8 minutes). Place apples, cut side down, in cream mix.
Cover and continue cooking, spooning sauce over apples occasionally, until apples are fork-tender.
Remove apples to individual dishes.
With wire whisk, whisk sauce until smooth.
Serve over apple halves.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients. Add chocolate chips. Set aside. Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Fill cupcake cups 1/3 full with chocolate batter.
Top with heaping teaspoonful of cream cheese batter. Sprinkle with sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 22 to 26 cupcakes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Place marshmallows and strawberry juice in a saucepan.
Heat slowly until marshmallows are melted.
Beat until smooth and fluffy and chill.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise together. Blend in strawberries, pineapple, and marshmallow mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze and serve over lettuce.

title: barbecued pecans
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven.
Remove from heat.
Add Worcestershire sauce, catsup and hot sauce, stirring well.
Add pecans, stirring to coat.
Bake in oven at 350° until crunchy. Add salt to taste.
Store in airtight container.

title: crabmeat ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a ball and chill. Serve with cocktail sauce.

title: tuna salad
directions: Blend the tuna and cabbage together with fork.
Stir in mayonnaise, sour cream, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Line a small container with lettuce; put in slice of pineapple, then pile cabbage/tuna mixture on top.
Sprinkle over paprika.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix well.
Make into patties like hamburgers.
Chill for an hour or so before cooking.
Makes 5 to 6 patties.
Fry in skillet with about 1/4 inch of oil (Crisco) in skillet until brown (about 5 minutes), then turn.
Brown on other side.
Lower heat.
Continue cooking, turning occasionally until done (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix broken up pretzels, 1 stick margarine and white sugar. Bake 10 minutes at 350° in 8 to 9-inch baking dish.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Beat Dream Whip separately according to package directions.
Combine with cream cheese mixture.
Spread on top of pretzel crust.
Top with 1 can pineapple pie filling.
Chill.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water, Karo and salt to soft ball stage. While this is cooking, beat egg whites. Pour 1/2 of cooked mixture into beaten egg whites and continue beating while the other half of the mixture cooks to hard ball (or crackle) stage.
Pour into mixture and beat until it loses its gloss.
Pour immediately into buttered dish.
Make on a clear day.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: I use Keebler's cookie crust pie shell.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan; cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in gelatin.
Pour over strawberries; mix well.
Pour into pie shell; refrigerate until set.
When ready to serve, spread topping over all.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese peas
directions: Cook peas according to directions on package.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Stir cornstarch and soy sauce into drained mushroom liquid.
Partially open peas and drain butter sauce into small saucepan.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook over low heat until slightly thickened.
(Stir constantly.)
Stir in peas and mushrooms.
Heat several minutes.
Serve hot over chow mein noodles.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate one hour before serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Put dressing and Salad Supreme on while spaghetti is hot.
Add rest of the ingredients after mixing well.

title: pineapple cake filling
directions: Mix all ingredients well; refrigerate for about 30 minutes. Spread on cake layers.

title: three bean dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 40 minutes.
Also can make in crock-pot.

title: microwave 100% bran muffins
directions: Mix bran and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Blend flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
Mix margarine and Egg Beaters into bran mixture.
Stir in flour mixture just until blended.
Stir in apples and raisins.
Fill 6 microwavable muffin pans 2/3 full.
Cook on High (100% power) 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, rotating pan after 1 minute.

title: squash parmesan
directions: Place yellow squash in shallow microwave-safe round glass baking dish.
Top with onion and zucchini.
