Sprinkle with cheese. Combine melted margarine, eggs, milk and pepper.
Pour over squash.
Do not stir.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Turn dish a half turn and cook on 50% power for 12 to 14 minutes or until almost set.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: best biscuit mix
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large mixer bowl.
With mixer on lowest speed, drop shortening by spoonfuls on top of flour mixture, until well blended.
Store in airtight container, glass is good.
(Do not refrigerate, not necessary.)
Keeps for months on pantry shelf.

title: microwave artichokes
directions: Wash thoroughly, allowing a small amount of water to cling to leaves.
Wrap in waxed paper and place on glass pie plate (or small glass dish).
Rotate dish one-quarter turn through cooking time.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes.
Rest, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: chili
directions: Broil hamburger; chop up fine.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Cook 1 cup presoaked navy beans with the onions until tender. Saute the celery for 5 minutes, then add.
Season with spices, being careful to let the bean and onion flavor predominate. Garnish with parsley or green onions.

title: wilson's favorite sweet potato pie(makes one 9-inch pie plus one smaller)
directions: Mix together thoroughly in order.
Then fold in 3 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into uncooked pastry shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then lower heat to 350°.
Bake until set and lightly browned, about 50 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in big iron frying pan.
Add brown sugar. Spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Lay sliced pineapple in bottom of pan and put cherries in center of pineapple.
Beat egg yolks and sugar.
Add flour, pineapple juice and baking soda.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and pour batter into skillet over fruit and brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and onion.
Add peppers and cream cheese.
Heat until mixed.
Wrap in shells.
Top with grated Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: icing for box cakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients with electric mixer.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pour pie filling into prepared crust.
Mix together oats, flour, sugar and butter.
Spread evenly on top of apple or other Lucky Leaf pie filling.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until top is browned.

title: cheeseburger roll
directions: Cook the ground beef until brown. Remove from heat and drain oil. Add the catsup, cheese, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well. Set aside.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Add the shortening to the flour mixture and cut into flour until the size of peas. Add the milk.
Mix quickly and lightly. Turn dough out onto floured board.
Knead. Roll into a rectangle 10 x 12-inches.
Spread filling to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Moisten edges with cold water. Roll up as a jelly roll. Seal edges, pinching ends together.
Place on a lightly greased shallow pan and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cucumber yogurt dip
directions: Put all ingredients, except cucumber in bowl, blend well with whisk.
Fold in cucumber, stirring to combine and refrigerate for up to 3 days.

title: macaroni-ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss together until blended.
Put in tomato cups and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: slaw to freeze
directions: Sprinkle salt over cabbage and stir well.
Let set 1 hour. Add pepper and celery; let set 20 minutes more.
Drain well.
Mix other ingredients and bring to boil.
Cool slightly; pour over cabbage mixture.
Put in bags and freeze.

title: slow-cooker chicken lasagna
directions: Press spinach between layers of paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Combine spinach, chicken, soup, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, milk, onion, mayo and salt in large bowl; stir mixture well.
Place 3 uncooked noodles in bottom of a lightly greased 5-quart electric slow cooker.
Spread 1/3 of chicken mixture over noodles; sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Layer with 3 more noodles, 1/2 chicken mixture and 1 cup cheese.
Layer remaining ingredients as above.
Cover and cook on high setting one hour. Reduce heat to low and cook 5 more hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Drain grease.
Boil noodles 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce to hamburger.
Melt cheese with small amount of milk to make smoother sauce.
Pour noodles in casserole dish.
Cover with hamburger and top with cheese sauce. Bake at 350° covered for 30 minutes.

title: hobo potatoes
directions: Cook and dice potatoes.
Cook bacon until crispy.
Chop onions and saute in margarine.
Chop up bacon.
Mix everything together. Place in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese dip for tortilla chips
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain.
Melt cheese and mix with all other ingredients.
Serve in crock-pot to keep dip warm.

title: baked vegetable casserole
directions: Toast bread, then roll into crumbs. Make a sauce with eggs, milk, flour, salt and pepper. Mix vegetables well. Layer ingredients in the following order: vegetables, crumbs, sauce and cheese. Repeat until all is used. Place hot melted butter on top and sprinkle with handful of corn flakes. Bake 20 to 40 minutes in an oven preheated to 375°. Serve hot. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together ingredients and let chill.

title: mom's custard pie
directions: Line prick pastry shell with a double thickness of heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 450 degrees for 8 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 5 minutes longer.
Remove from the oven and set aside.
Separate 1 egg; set the white aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat the yolk and remaining eggs just until combined.
Blend in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Stir in milk.
Beat reserved egg white until stiff peaks form; fold into egg mixture.
Carefully pour into crust.
Cover edges of pie with foil.
Bake at 350 for 25 minutes.
Remove foil bake 15-20 minutes longer or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Store in the refrigerator.

title: lasagna
directions: Melt oil in a large skillet.
Add ground beef, pepperoni and garlic.
Mix well and cook until lightly browned.
Add spaghetti sauce or pizza mix, tomato paste, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until well blended.

title: cheesecake topped brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs. Spread into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In small mixing bowl, beat cheese, butter and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then egg and vanilla until smooth. Pour evenly over brownie batter.
Bake 45 minutes or until top is browned.
Cool.
Spread with frosting.
Cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Makes 36 to 40 brownies.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs; mix one at a time.
Add flour and milk.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Put in greased tube pan.
Start in a cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1/4 cup of soup.
Shape into patties. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes.
Mix rest of soup with 1/4 cup water.
Spoon over patties.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Form in small balls about 1/2 inch round.
Place in deep skillet.
Cook about 15 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from skillet when done; set aside for later.
Pour cooking oil in clean skillet and let heat.
Pour flour, salt and pepper in oil; stir until browned.
Add milk, stirring until smooth.
Add a can of water, stirring until smooth. Add more water if needed.
Place meatballs in gravy and serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain excess fluid from beans, corn and peas and combine.
Add onion, pepper and celery. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine sugar, vinegar and oil. Stir and pour over vegetables.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 10 hours. Serve cold.

title: ranch stuffed potatoes(serves 8)
directions: Scoop out inside of 4 baked potatoes.
Combine with 1/4 cup sour cream and 1 ounce package of Hidden Valley Ranch dry salad dressing mix.
Fill potato skins with mixture.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant, cut into small pieces and boil in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Saute onions in margarine until tender but not brown.
Add eggplant, tomatoes, cheese and 1/3 cup bread crumbs.
Add eggs, cooking and stirring until eggs are cooked.
Pour into baking dish and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a large pan. Remove from oven and punch holes in it with a wooden spoon. Immediately pour over cake a mixture of the condensed milk, cream of coconut and 1 package of the fresh coconut.
Let this soak in, then spread the undrained pineapple over the top.
Let cake cool. Mix the other package of coconut with 1 package whipped topping and spread over top of cake.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Mix 1 cup sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake until toothpick in center comes out clean, 50 or 60 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.
Cool completely before slicing. Store tightly covered.

title: cinnamon cream cheese cookies
directions: In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt. In large bowl, using wooden spoon, cream together butter, cream cheese and sugar until combined.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours until firm enough to shape.
To prepare topping, stir together sugar and cinnamon in a custard cup.
Shape dough into 1-inch diameter balls.
Roll each ball in topping to coat lightly. Place balls on prepared baking sheets, leaving about 2-inches between balls.

Bake 1 sheet at a time, at 350°, for 10 to 14 minutes or until bottoms of cookies are very lightly browned. Remove baking sheet to a wire rack and cool for about 3 minutes. Using metal spatula, transfer cookies to rack and cool completely. Repeat until all dough is used.
When cool, store cookies in an airtight container.
Makes about 45 cookies.

title: egg strata
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up bread and put on the bottom of the pan.
Mix the eggs, milk, cheese and other ingredients together; pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dump cake
directions: Put the crushed pineapple with juice in the bottom of the pan. Add the cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle on the nuts.
Sprinkle on the dry cake mix.
Cut butter into chunks and drop on top. Sprinkle brown sugar over all.
Add more nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot-milk sponge cake
directions: Sift
together
flour,
baking
powder
and
salt.
Add butter to
milk;
keep hot.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon-colored, about
minutes at high speed on mixer.
Gradually add
sugar, beating constantly at medium speed 4 to 5 minutes. Quickly add sifted ingredients to egg mixture; stir just until blended.
Stir in
hot
milk mixture and vanilla; blend well. Pour into paper-lined 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool cake in pan 15 minutes;
remove to rack.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; cool.

title: italian seashells
directions: Boil the seashell noodles 7 minutes. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Cook the hamburger; drain off grease.
Mix all ingredients (except Mozzarella cheese) in a large mixing bowl.
Butter a large 9 x 15 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour in mixture. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: butter baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Halve potatoes lengthwise; then slice crosswise into 1/8-inch slices.
Immediately line up in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan with slices overlapping.
Pour butter and onion over potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake 20 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes more, until cheese melts and is slightly brown.

title: hearth loaf
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle yeast over water; set aside 5 minutes. Stir in 4 cups of all-purpose flour, the whole wheat flour, oat bran flakes (reserving 2 tablespoons), cornmeal, honey and salt, until combined.

title: easy 7-minute frosting
directions: Mix egg whites, sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla flavoring with boiling water.
Beat for 10 minutes to 12 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Yield:
icing for 3-layer cake.

title: microwave chocolate cake(about 8 servings)
directions: Grease round micro-proof baking dish, 7 1/4 x 2 1/4-inch or 8 x 1 1/2-inch; line bottom with plastic wrap.
In small micro-proof bowl, combine cocoa and 1/3 cup water.
Microwave on High (full power) 40 to 50 seconds or until slightly thickened.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Precook chicken and broccoli.
First line bottom of greased pan with broccoli, then chicken.
Mix together, soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour this over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Sprinkle paprika (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Prepare corn muffin mix per package directions except add 1/2 cup fried onions.
Spoon around casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top corn bread with cheese and rest of onions.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet and drain. Add onion, mushrooms and green pepper, cooking over medium heat until onions are translucent. Cook rice according to package directions. Place cooked rice, sausage mixture and cream of mushroom soup in large bowl and mix thoroughly. Place in lightly greased baking dish and top with shredded cheese. Bake in 350° oven for approximately 25 minutes or until completely heated and cheese is melted.

title: cocoa pies
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar, flour, cocoa, salt and vanilla. Mix well and add milk.
Cook until thick and pour into 2 baked pie crusts. Cover with meringue.
Brown lightly.

title: salsa
directions: Drain liquid from stewed tomatoes.
Dice onion and jalapeno peppers.
Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend for 10 seconds (if blended longer, salsa becomes runny).
Chill in refrigerator, preferably overnight.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: erin's corn(servings:  6)
directions: Combine corn, onion, salt, milk, butter and cream cheese in a covered saucepan.
Start cooking on high until vegetable steams, then turn down heat to low and continue cooking about 15 minutes. If doubled, do not double the milk, butter or cream cheese.

title: las vegas flamingo
directions: Combine all ingredients except liquor.
Pour liquor into each glass; add ice and about 6 ounces fruit juice mixture.
Makes 8 servings.

title: party pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Mix several times.
Serve cold. Makes 12 servings.

title: poppy seed sherry bundt cake
directions: Butter and flour a Bundt pan; shake out excess flour.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream, melted butter, sherry and poppy seed.
Beat 5 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool completely in pan.
Invert onto platter to serve.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and arrange on bottom and around sides of a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.

title: chicken jumbolia
directions: Cook celery, onion and green pepper slowly in margarine until soft.
Add chicken broth or water, uncooked rice, tomatoes (cut up with juice) and chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Flavor with spices. Turn down and cook for 40 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: barbecued lima beans
directions: Cover beans with water.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Next day, drain; measure drained liquid and replace with fresh water. Turn into Dutch oven.
Add salt.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour or until beans are tender.
Meanwhile make sauce.
Saute bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from pan and drain.
In hot bacon drippings, saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Add barbecue sauce, tomato sauce and brown sugar.
Add to beans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with bacon pieces for last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then turn down to 325° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight, stirring once in awhile to make sure all carrots are covered in sauce.

title: glazed corned beef(adapted from silver palate cookbook)
directions: Place corned beef in large pot with boiling water.
Bring to boil, lower heat, cover partially and simmer as slowly as possible for about 3 hours or until very tender when tested with a fork. Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix preserves, mustard and sugar together in small bowl.
When meat is done, remove from pot and drain. Place meat on ovenproof serving dish and pour preserves mixture over it, coating thoroughly.
Bake corned beef for 30 minutes or until glaze is crisp and brown.
Serve hot or at room temperature. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Cook squash in salted water until tender.
Drain and put in dish and chop it with fork a little bit. Add the beaten egg, onion and cheese to squash.
Put cracker crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in butter.
Pour in casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: pecan crisp cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs. Add flour, then stir in nuts. Drop by teaspoonful on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: traditional rocky road fudge
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine sugar, butter and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture comes to a boil (7 to 10 minutes).
Boil and stir until candy thermometer reaches 228° or small amount of mixture dropped onto ice forms a 2-inch soft thread.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted. Stir in cream until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in marshmallows and peanuts, leaving a marble effect.
Spread in lightly buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover; refrigerate until cooled.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: graham cracker sandwiches
directions: Blend oleo, milk, sugar and egg in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add coconut, pecans and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well; spread over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers on top.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix Oreos and butter together.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan; press down.
Put in freezer.
While cookie crust is freezing, prepare sauce.

title: spiced tea
directions: Wrap cloves and cinnamon bark in cloth bag or tie square of cotton with string.
Put bag in 1 1/2-quart enamel pan, 3/4 filled with water, sinking bag in water.
While water is heating, mix orange juice or Tang, lemon juice and sugar in large tea pot or pitcher.
When water is boiling, remove from heat and submerse tea bags in water.
Cover pan and steep tea fo 20 minutes.
Pour hot water into tea pot.
Keep refilling pan with hot faucet water, squeezing flavor out of spices and tea bags.
Pour second pan of water into tea pot.
Repeat 1 or 2 more times.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Excellent for the holidays!

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, shortening and sugar. Add sifted flour and salt with milk; blend well. Add flavorings and baking powder. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Cook in 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour. Immediately run knife around sides. Cool and remove from pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and peppers.
Drain.
Saute mushrooms and zucchini.
Spread all into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: my grandma's thunder cake
directions: Cream together at one time the vanilla, shortening and sugar. Blend in egg yolks. Beat whites until they are stiff, then fold in.
Mix dry mixture into cream mixture. Bake in 2 greased and floured round pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Frost with chocolate butter frosting. Top with strawberries.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake in 13 x 5 x 9-inch pan according to directions. Let cool slightly. Poke holes in cake with end of wooden spoon, being careful not to go to bottom of pan. Mix 2 cans of creams together and drizzle over warm cake. Let cool completely and spread top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle coconut over top. Cover and refrigerate until next day (if you can wait).

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Drain fruit thoroughly.
Combine with beaten egg.
Add fruit mixture to flour mixture and stir until well blended.
Batter should be smooth.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and nuts. Sprinkle over cake.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Add mashed potatoes to all of the other ingredients and mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mary howard's rice pudding(my very own)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and raisins and add cooked rice.
Stir around, must be soupy; add more milk if needed.
Pour in baking dish and sprinkle top with nutmeg and dot with butter. (Do not stir anymore.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cook long enough to (kinda) set.
It can be overcooked and it makes it dry.
If this happens here is a delicious sauce and easy to make.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute in butter the onion, add Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup. Boil broccoli until hot.
Bake at 350° until hot for 30 minutes.

title: apple bavarian torte
directions: Cut butter into very small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and mix with pastry blender until it resembles coarse meal.
Press into pan and bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: fast banana cake
directions: Put all together in large bowl; mix well by hand.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° checking at about 45 minutes.

title: patio punch
directions: Chill 3 1/2 cups ginger ale.
Combine Kool-Aid and sugar in large container.
Adding 4 quarts water stirring while adding, stir until dissolved.
Add thawed juice and lemonade.
Add strawberries and chill until serving time.
Pour over decorated ice block or cubes in a large punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale down side of bowl slowly.
Stir gently.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: kathy's calzone
directions: Let dough rise.
Roll out to form an oblong.
Layer cheese down the center of the dough.
Add drained, roasted peppers and then pepperoni on top.
Fold over one side and then the other side, like wrapping a package.
Pinch ends and along the seam.

title: wedding mints (butter)
directions: Combine ingredients and make into balls.
Press into molds.

title: traveler's corned beef buns(makes 8 servings)
directions: Soak onion in water for 5 minutes.
Add next 6 ingredients. Mix until well blended.
Spread on buns.

title: chinese mushroom steak
directions: Brown meat in oil; push steak to one side.
Blend flour into remaining fat.
Gradually stir in remaining ingredients, except green pepper and mushrooms. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add green pepper and mushrooms; cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips and walnuts.
Spread batter on large greased and floured cookie pan.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice the eggplants into 1/4-inch slices.
Peel the eggplants (optional) first, dip eggplant into eggs and then cover them with bread crumbs and put it into a pan of hot oil.
When the eggplant is golden brown, put 1 layer into a casserole dish.
Add Ricotta or cream cheese to taste; add tomato sauce and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Keep adding layers until the dish is full. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken with apple juice
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Add apple juice, water, lemon juice and cumin.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: crock-pot teriyaki pork
directions: In crock-pot, combine juice, vinegar, soy sauce, sugar and ginger.
Add pork.
Cook 4 hours on high (6 to 8 hours on low). Strain juice, bring to boil and thicken with cornstarch and water. Mix until bubbly.
Serve with rice and salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tuna lasagna
directions: Combine tomatoes, tomato paste, spaghetti sauce mix, oregano, sugar and garlic in 2-quart heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tuna; set aside.
Place 1/2 of the noodles on bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1/3 of the tuna sauce, 1/2 of the cottage cheese and 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with tuna sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In large bowl, combine cooked chicken, onions and chilies.
Mix in seasonings to taste, along with sour cream (enough to more than coat the chicken) and shredded cheese.

title: poppy seed dough and fillings
directions: Combine the lukewarm water, 3 tablespoons sugar and the yeast. Beat
the eggs, sugar and salt together.
Combine this mixture with
the
yeast mixture.
Add the warm milk, 1/2 at a time, the Crisco
and
flour (add 6 cups first, then 4 cups). Grease pans. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: horiatiki salata (greece)(summer salad)
directions: Place tomatoes, cucumber, onion and peppers in a large salad bowl.
Shake together the olive oil, vinegar, salt and pepper. Pour dressing over the salad.
Place wedges of Feta cheese and olives on top of salad.
Add sprinkles of parsley over the top of the salad as final garnish.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana delight
directions: Whip the whipping cream and layer as follows:

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and shortening over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until brownies start to pull away from sides of pan.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve Jell-O in water.
Stir in pie filling and pineapple. Chill until set.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar. Spread over Jell-O and chill.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes, set aside.
Fry bacon slowly; drain on paper, crumble and set aside.
Saute onion in bacon fat until golden brown.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Carefully stir in the potatoes and bacon.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand until ready to serve.
Reheats well.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rolled turkey breast with red pepper stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat butter in frying pan.
Add onion, garlic and basil.
Remove from heat and stir in salt, pepper, bread crumbs and parsley.

title: eagle brand fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients, then pour into bread pan that has been greased, then wax papered, then greased again.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; remove wax paper.
Slice thin.

title: simmered corned beef
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, place brisket with water.
Slice onion over brisket and add garlic and bay leaves.
Cover; microwave on High for 25 minutes.
Turn brisket over.
Re-cover; microwave on Low for 60 to 70 minutes, turning brisket over after 30 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs; beat until light. Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth; add vanilla and milk and bananas. Beat until mixed together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13x9 inch greased and floured pan.
Icing: 1/4 cup margarine, 3 Tbsp. brown sugar, 3 Tbsp.
canned milk, 1 cup chopped pecans. Melt together over low heat until very hot, but do not boil. Then add 1 cup powdered sugar. Add chopped nuts and spread on cake while cake is still warm.

title: bourbon carrots
directions: Cut carrots diagonally into 1/4-inch slices.
In heavy saucepan, combine carrots, granulated sugar, 1 1/2 tablespoons butter and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to a simmer, cover and cook, until carrots are tender when pierced with a knife, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain carrots, taste and add more salt, if needed.
Add pepper.

title: hot peanuts
directions: Roast peanuts in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Drain. Combine remaining ingredients and mix with peanuts.
Let cool. Store in airtight container.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Heat both raspberries and sugar separately in 300° oven for 20 minutes.
Gently fold sugar into raspberries.
Refrigerate and use as a spread on toast, English muffins, etc.

title: microwave cauliflower au gratin
directions: In casserole dish, put cauliflower and water.
Microwave for 12 minutes, covered.
Let stand 3 minutes.
In another casserole dish (3-quart), put butter and onion; microwave for 5 minutes. Stir once or twice during cooking.
Add cauliflower after draining it.
Stir.
You may put in 7 x 11-inch casserole dish or leave in 3-quart dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, then Parmesan cheese. Microwave for 4 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix together potato flakes, boiling water, salt and margarine. Add milk and mix until smooth.
Add margarine, cream cheese, sour cream and chives.
When mixed smooth, pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish, sprinkle with Salad Supreme and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Can be mixed in advance, refrigerated and then baked.

title: sweet and sour hawaiian pork chops
directions: Spray large skillet. Saute onion and pepper. Remove from skillet. Mix flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag. Add chops one at a time; shake to coat meat. Brown chops in skillet. Place pineapple slice on top of each chop. Sprinkle with onion and pepper. Combine vinegar, ketchup and juice to make sauce. Pour over chops. Simmer 45 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine water and margarine in saucepan, bring to boil.

Boil for 2 min. Stir in flour until well blended (about 1 min.) Remove from heat,cool completely. Beat in eggs. Mix well. Spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until slighltly golden in color. Whip vanilla pudding and whipping cream until fluffy. Slice cream puff across middle. Fill with pudding mixture.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Line one tube pan or 2 loaf pans with Glad Wrap.
Mix all ingredients together and press into pans.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Pull out of pans and wrap in foil.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Add ingredients one at a time in apples.
Turn into pie crust.
Dot with butter or margarine. Cover with top crust.
Seal and flute.
Cut slits into crust. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 425°.
Cover with aluminum foil. Remove during last 15 minutes.

title: tater tot dish
directions: Fry hamburger, onions, mushrooms and celery together and drain.
Layer hamburger mix on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of soup, then shredded cheese, then hamburger.
Repeat with soup, sour cream and cheese.
Top with Tater Tots about 10 minutes before serving so they may brown.
Set oven at 375°.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: banana-pineapple pudding pops
directions: Mix banana, pineapple and yogurt in blender for about 30 seconds or until smooth.
Gradually add the powdered instant vanilla pudding; blend well.
Freeze in freezer pop containers or small paper cups.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: overnight fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, then 3 cups flour with baking powder.
Take 1 cup of flour and mix with nuts and fruit. Add this and extract to rest of batter.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Grease a tube pan.
Pour in mixture and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Bake 3 1/2 hours.

title: mocho dip
directions: Brown hamburger; take off burner and add onion, taco sauce and cheese mix.
Divide can of refried beans in two; layer in 2 pie plates and top with hamburger mixture.
Slice ripe olives on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with sour cream and serve with Doritos.

title: good dumplins
directions: Stir flour, baking powder and salt together in mixing bowl. Combine milk and salad oil; add dry ingredients until moist.
Drop by tablespoon into boiling broth.
Cover tightly; return to boil. Reduce heat; do not lift cover.
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes.

title: snowballs or wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in flour, pecans, orange rind and vanilla.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300°F for 35 minutes.
Cool slightly and roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: easy bake pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops on both sides.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove pork chops from skillet and place into glass baking dish.
Cut green pepper into quarters and each quarter into slices.
Scatter on top of pork chops.
Cut onion into wedges and separate layer.
Also scatter on top of pork chops.
Pour mushroom soup and 1 cup of white wine over pork chops and vegetables.

title: real texas chili
directions: Heat oil in 4-quart kettle or heavy-bottom pan over medium heat.
Add beef, stirring frequently, with a wooden spoon until meat changes color, but does not brown.
Lower heat; stir in garlic.

title: beef and bean tostadas
directions: Prepare ground beef according to directions on seasoning mix package.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place tosdata shells on baking sheet; warm in oven 5 to 7 minutes.
Spread each shell with 1/4 cup of beans.
Top with 1 or 2 tablespoons of ground beef mixture, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and taco sauce.
Makes 12 tostadas.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolk.
Mash yolks and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Add ham, carrots, mayonnaise and mustard.
Stir well.
Fill egg halves with mixture. Chill.
Sprinkle with paprika or garnish with pimento or fresh parsley.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: meat loaf in sauce
directions: Mix the beef, eggs,
onion, 1/2 the tomato sauce, salt, Worcestershire sauce and bread crumbs together well and put in a loaf pan.
Mix the other
half
of the tomato sauce with the vinegar, mustard, brown sugar
and
water.
Pour over the meat mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lazy chocolate pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and chocolate together.
Let cool.
Mix in Cool Whip and pour into pie shell.

title: roman pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage with chopped onion.
Drain grease.
Mix meat with sauce from pizza mix and enough ketchup to make spreadable.
Fix dough.
Spread 1 package Mozzarella cheese on dough.
Spread meat.
Add pepperoni.
Add mushrooms and bell pepper cut in rings.
Top with remaining package of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° until crust browns.

title: wet-heavy cornbread
directions: Instead of eggs, can use 3/4 cup Egg Beaters.
Can use 1 tablespoon plus 1 1/2 teaspoons of Sweet 'N low instead of sugar. Can use skim and oleo instead of evaporated milk.

title: hot dog roll-ups
directions: Melt margarine.
Place bread on a cookie sheet.
Use a basting brush to spread about 1/2 of the margarine on the bread pieces, then spread mustard or mayonnaise on the bread.
Top each slice of bread with 1 cheese triangle and a hot dog.
Fold bread over to form a triangle shape.
Fasten with 2 toothpicks, poking through the bread and hot dogs.
Brush the remaining margarine on the top of each "bread triangle."
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve with ketchup and chips.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in corn; remove from heat.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.

title: ham balls
directions: Lightly greased jelly roll pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Place on pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: batter for fried fish
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix all ingredients together and let stand at room temperature for 2 hours.
Leftovers can be refrigerated up to 3 weeks. Good for onion rings, too.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Mix all soups, Ro-Tel and melted cheese together in a bowl.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with Doritos. Pour a layer of hamburger.
Pour a layer of soup mixture.
Repeat. Cover with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: andy and tori's m&m caramel apples
directions: Melt caramels with water in double boiler; stir until smooth. Put a stick into a side of each apple.
Dip apple into caramels. Coat well.
Set on waxed paper.
Apply M&M's generously.
(Pig out.)

title: jewish cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Makes about 120 cookies.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add green pepper (cut up) and cut up onion. Cook until pepper starts to soften.
Add stewed tomatoes, salt, pepper and garlic.
Bring to boil.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni.
Cook a few minutes longer.

title: cheese sauce for potatoes and veggies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over stove, watching closely to avoid darkening.
Add flour to the pan to make a very thick paste. Add milk to the paste, stir well and add cheese, cubed.
Great over cooked cubed potatoes, cooked broccoli, etc.

title: meatless taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread over pie plate. Top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and onions.
Serve with taco or tortilla chips.

title: spareribs
directions: Mix ingredients together, except spareribs, in a pot over burner until boiling.
Pour over spareribs.
Put in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious!

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: In saucepan, stir sugar over low heat until melted and golden brown.
Stir in carefully hot water and brown sugar.
Cook to 238° or until a little dropped into cold water forms a soft ball. Pour over 12 cups popped corn, mixing gently to coat well.
Press into balls.

title: my italian cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, rum or brandy and vanilla together until creamy, then add the Ricotta cheese, a little at a time.
This you use creamy and not beating until all is creamy.
Butter a lasagna pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cool and put in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Form into walnut size balls. Bake on cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in covered jar or canister.
Shake occasionally until oil is absorbed.
They taste better if made and set for a day.

title: vermont butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually, beat until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts; beat well.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheets.
Top each cookie with a walnut half.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add pineapple, mixing well.
Fold in whipping cream.
Pour in pie crust.
Chill overnight.

title: banana-pineapple ice cream
directions: Wash and chill container and dash for 3 or 4-quart ice cream freezer.
Combine bananas, sugar, orange and lemon peels and lemon and lime juices.
Blend thoroughly.
Set aside for 10 minutes.

title: hot tuna hero
directions: Combine tuna, mayonnaise, sour cream, parsley, lemon juice and garlic salt.
Slice bread lengthwise; spread with margarine. Place cheese and tuna mix between bread halves.
Wrap in foil. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: san francisco stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add beef; cook and stir until no longer pink.
In small bowl, combine jelly, cornstarch and mustard; blend well.
Add jelly mixture and frozen vegetables to meat.
Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, one egg and melted butter.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and remaining 2 eggs.
Pour over cake dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into squares.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Crush cookies and pat 2/3 into a 9 x
13-inch pan.
Beat sugar, lemon juice, egg whites and thawed strawberries for 8 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip and spread over crumbs in pan.
Top with rest of cookie crumbs.
Freeze. Do not defrost to serve.

title: blue cheese cream cheese spread
directions: Mix ingredients together. This is better after it sets 12 to 24 hours in the refrigerator. Serve with crackers. Top with ring of sweet hot pepper, if desired.

title: corn muffin bean bake
directions: In skillet, brown hot dogs, celery and onions in oil until tender.
Add beans, ketchup, brown sugar and mustard.
Heat; stir. Pour into baking dish.
Mix muffin mix, egg and milk.
Spoon around edge of dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crispy peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter or margarine in a medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Pour in sugar, then Rice Krispies. Blend well.
Chill and roll into desirable size balls.

title: rocky road s'mores bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Press in bottom of a greased 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and cut in bars.
Makes 16 servings.

title: oyster cracker munchies
directions: Mix all together and pour over crackers.
Coat crackers and let set.
(Do not bake.)

title: squash dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Saute onions, celery and green pepper in butter.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: dill pickles(very old recipe)
directions: Have jars and lids very hot.
Put in the bottom of each jar a grape leaf, garlic and dill.
Heat water, alum, salt and vinegar to boiling.
Pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: souperburger sandwiches
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef and onion until beef is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, ketchup and black pepper.
Reduce heat to low.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Serve on buns.
Preparation time: 5 minutes.
Cook time:
15 minutes.

title: cheese munchies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate room temperature cheese and cream with butter/margarine.
Mix together in small bowl the flour, salt and paprika.
Add to first mixture and add Tabasco.
Mix well. Last, mix in carefully with a fork, the corn flakes, trying not to crush them too much.
Break off small pieces of the dough (about a tablespoon) and roll like a marble.
Press down lightly onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Easy and good.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Cook chicken.
Tear chunks of meat and put into pot.
Cover meat with broth.
Add chiles and onions.
Cook until broth has cooked away some.
Warm flour tortillas and put a couple of tablespoons of chicken in the middle.
Sprinkle some cheese on, roll up and serve.

title: deep fried shrimp
directions: Heat oil over steady high heat in deep skillet.
Mix flour, baking powder, egg and milk.
Beat well until mixture runs smoothly from a spoon.
(You may need to add more milk or flour.) Dip individual pieces of shrimp into flour mixture.
Drop into hot oil.
Shrimp is done when outside is golden brown.
Easy and quick.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together butter, 2 cups flour and powdered sugar; press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. While this is baking, use a mixer to beat eggs, sugar, 6 tablespoons flour and lemon juice. Take pan out of the oven and pour lemon mixture over crust and bake another 20 minutes. Let cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Combine all but the chicken in a small pan and bring to boil. Pour over chicken pieces and marinate 2 hours or longer in refrigerator.
You may grill chicken outdoors or bake in oven.
Use sauce to baste.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
You can also use this sauce to marinate steaks.

title: pear salad
directions: Place pear halves on lettuce.
Fill centers with mint jelly. Top with 1/4 teaspoon mayonnaise and a cherry.
Yields 4 servings.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Bake for 10 minutes, then down to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Simple but good.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: sausage mushroom appetizers
directions: Remove mushroom stems (discard or save for another use); set caps aside.
In a large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients. Stuff into the mushroom caps.
Place in two greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dishes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 16 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield 4 dozen.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a rolling boil.
Serve over meat or in a side dish.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients by hand DO NOT USE MIXER.
Bake at 350 for 55 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients in a doubled plastic food bag. Shake well.
Prepare a 10 x 15 x 3/4-inch pan with Pam or wipe it well with oil.
Run a cut-up fryer chicken under cold water and let excess water drip or put the wet chicken pieces into a colander and drain a few minutes.
Dredge pieces into the flour mixture by placing each piece, one at a time, into the bag of seasoned flour.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice in baking dish.
Cover with a layer of potatoes and a layer of grated cheese for two layers.
Pour soup and milk over potatoes plus cheese mixture.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: monterey chicken
directions: Flour chicken and brown in melted butter 3 to 5 minutes on each side.
Remove from pan and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In the pan with butter, add mushrooms and onions; saute about 10 minutes.
Add spices, chicken broth, wine and 1/4 cup cheese. Cook until thickens.
Pour over chicken and cover with 3/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips. Toss. Put in greased 1 1/2 quart casserole or 8 x 12 inch glass pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with chips and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: fruit cake fingers
directions: Mix flavoring and salt with milk.
Pour over remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans, greased well and lined with several layers of brown paper.
Bake 30 minutes at 250°, then at 275° for 20 minutes.
Cool before cutting into fingers or bars.

title: lite chocolate mousse
directions: Put chocolate and coffee in small pot over low heat until chocolate is almost melted.
Remove from heat and stir until smooth.
Add Kahlua and Amaretto.

title: pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in one teaspoon salt, sugar and 2 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise until double, 45 to 60 minutes. (Dough is ready when indentation remains when touched.)

title: spiff burgers
directions: Peel banana and combine with milk and corn flakes in bowl. Mix in hamburger to thorough consistency.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Make patties of desired size.
Taste great cooked on grill.
Season to taste.

title: brown bag apple pie
directions: Prepare apples in large bowl.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over apples.
Pour in pie shell and drizzle with lemon juice.
Combine remaining flour and sugar.
Cut in butter.
Sprinkle over apples to cover the top. Put in heavy bag.
Fold end.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: oyster souffle
directions: Saute celery in margarine.
Place a layer of cracker crumbs and a layer of oysters in a 2-quart casserole.	Sprinkle with salt and pepper and celery.	Repeat layer until all oyster are used.
Top with 1/2 cup crumbs.
Pour broth over oyster mixture; let stand 30 minutes.
Bake at 350 degrees 10 minutes.
Pour eggs on top and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Return to oven again and bake 15-20 minutes or until eggs are done.
Serves 4-6.

title: sausage casserole dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into large well-greased casserole bowl with cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade rice pilaf
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, saute noodles in butter until golden. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and cover.
Let cook on high until boiling.
Boil for 5 minutes, then reduce heat to a simmer. Simmer for about 20 to 25 minutes, until all water is absorbed. Allow to sit for at least 15 minutes before serving.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle flour on top.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: undercover sweet corn
directions: Peel husks back, but do not remove from ears.
Remove silk. Soak ears with husks in cold water for 20 minutes.
Mix margarine and cream cheese.
Dry surface of kernels; spread on cheese mixture.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Close husks over ears and wrap individually in foil.
Place in preheated oven on low.
Turn ears every 5 minutes.
Check for doneness after 30 minutes. Flavor is unusual; try it!

title: microwave lasagna(simple to sensational)
directions: Spread half of sauce on bottom of pan.
Lay 1 layer of noodles, side by side.
Next layer half of the spinach on top of the noodles followed by the Ricotta cheese.
Make another layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat except lay noodles in the opposite direction. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Leave one small corner vented.
Cook at Medium-high for 25 minutes (for a medium pan).
Leave covered as it cools, cut into squares.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring; add to first mixture.
Mix salt and vanilla to buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour to first mixture.
When well mixed next with a spoon (not mixer), add baking soda and vinegar.
Mix in well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle in crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour condensed milk over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut in about 16 squares.

title: sausage casserole dinner
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet.
Place in bottom of casserole.
Add alternate layers of macaroni, vegetables and seasonings.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with cut up raw vegetables.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak dried apricots in warm water for 30 minutes.
Save water. Sift together flour, wheat germ, rolled oats, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add egg, oil, 3/4 cup of the saved apricot water, walnuts and the coarsely chopped apricots.
Place batter in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Store for 24 hours before serving.

title: pretzel candy
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water; add pretzels and peanuts.
Pour on waxed paper covered cookie sheet.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: poor man's soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions, butterbeans, cabbage, fat back meat, tomatoes and margarine until potatoes are done.
Then add corn and cook for about 5 more minutes.

title: bacon-cheddar cheese scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In a medium skillet, cook the bacon, stirring until crisp, about 5 minutes.
Remove with a slotted spoon and drain well on a paper towel.
Into a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt.
Cut in the butter, cheese, onions, and pepper with a pastry blender or fork, and work just unnail it starts to form lumps and come together.
Add the bacon.
Add 1 cup of the cream and work just until it becomes sticky dough, being careful not to overwork.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together and place between 2 cookies.

title: turkey chili
directions: In a 4 quart Dutch oven cook the turkey until no longer pink. Drain
off	fat.
Stir
in	undrained tomatoes, drained kidney beans, tomato sauce, onion, wine, chili powder, parsley flakes, basil,
oregano,
black pepper, cinnamon, garlic, red pepper
and bay
leaf.	Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer about
2	hours, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with green or yellow sweet peppers, cut into rings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni as directed on package.
Drain and let cool.
Mix sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Set aside and cool.
Chop the onion and pepper.
Grate the carrots.
Add the mayonnaise.
After macaroni is cooled, add vinegar and sugar mixture, onion, pepper and carrots.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Best when refrigerated overnight.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until color changes.
Put crumbled cornbread and other bread in large mixing bowl.
Add onions, celery, eggs and seasonings.
Mix. Add chicken broth; mix well.
Spray a 2-quart baking dish with Pam.
Add mixture.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until mixture begins to brown. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate whoopie pies(makes about 4 dozen pies)
directions: To make sour milk, put 1 tablespoon of white vinegar in a measuring cup; fill up to the 1 cup line with milk.

title: walnut broccoli stir-fry
directions: Brown tofu in 2 tablespoons oil.
Bring water to boil; add salt and boil carrots and broccoli 1 minute.
Drain; reserve. Saute onions in 2 tablespoons oil, then add mushrooms and walnuts. Increase heat and add carrots and broccoli.
Add tofu cubes. Stir.
To reserved vegetable stock, add cornstarch, soy sauce and pepper.
Pour over tofu/vegetable; cook until cornstarch is clear. Serve over rice and add chemical heat by using chili oil.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together carefully.
Refrigerate a while before serving.

title: high hat chicken with a heavenly gravy
directions: Just smother and cook chicken in this mushroom gravy!

title: ham balls
directions: Mix in blender until well blended and make into balls.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and garlic salt together in a large mixing bowl.
Put in a 2 1/2-quart greased casserole or a 13 x 9-inch greased dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, coffee cream and homogenized milk with 2 cups sugar.
Mix 1 cup sugar with mashed peaches.
Pour milk mixture into gallon freezer can.
Freeze until mixture is partially frozen. Add peaches, then complete the freezing process. Remove dasher.
Pack ice cream firmly in freezer can.
Store in freezer to ripen.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Sprinkle chili powder and seasoning mix.
Stir.
Add V-8 juice and water; simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: christmas quiche
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Press hash browns to cover bottom and sides of plate.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Crisp under broiler 7 to 9 minutes.
Crumble bacon over hash browns.
Add 2 tablespoons diced onion if you wish.
Spread cheese over bacon.
Add milk to beaten eggs.
Mix well and pour over cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 325° for 20 more minutes.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat again.
Add oil and vanilla; beat.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well; pour into greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, frost with Vanilla Butter Frosting.

title: oatmeal mix to make and store
directions: Mix ingredients and store in airtight container.
Add a generous 1/2 cup of mix to 1 cup of water for 1 serving of oatmeal. Microwave on High for 2 minutes until thick, stirring after each minute.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.
The cake will rise and then fall, so don't worry.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: strawberry bars
directions: In a bowl stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Mix in oatmeal.
Cut in butter until mixture forms coarse crumbs.
Beat egg and milk.
Gradually add egg mixture to flour mixture, mixing until well blended.
Spread about half of the dough in a greased or nonstick 8-inch pan.
Spread evenly with jam.
Drop remaining dough evenly by spoonfuls over jam. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into bars while still warm.
Sift lightly with powdered sugar.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Cut up lettuce, onions and celery.
Add mandarin oranges. When ready to serve, add dressing to salad and add almond topping. Don't add dressing until just ready to serve.

title: sweet potatoes balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Roll your marshmallows up in your hands with your sweet potatoes, letting the potatoes cover the marshmallows, then roll the sweet potatoes balls in a pan of coconut.
Put on a cookie sheet and bake in oven until brown and then serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Arrange dough slices slightly overlapping on foil-lined 14-inch pizza pan or 15 x 10 x 1-inch pizza pan or 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Press edges of cookies to seal.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Slide crust from foil onto serving plate.

title: mummy cases
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut 2 hot dogs in half, first one way and then the other, so you have 8 pieces.
Unroll crescent roll dough.
Divide dough into 4 rectangles.
Close holes in middle by pinching together.
Put 1 cheese slice on each rectangle.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon bacon on top of each cheese slice.
Put one whole hot dog on top of each pile.
Place a piece of hot dog on each side of whole hot dog to make body section wider.
Roll it up in the dough, pressing edges together to make mummy shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make deep bandage marks on dough with knife and poke eye holes with pointed object.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: imogene salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O into water.
Chill to egg white consistency. Cream sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Whip Jell-O with cream cheese and add Cool Whip.
Whip until smooth.

title: chicken polynesian
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Marinate 4 to 5 hours, turning and basting chicken several times.
Bake at 350° in marinade for 20 minutes (skin side down).
Turn chicken (skin side up) and bake additional 20 minutes.
Baste with marinade while baking.
Serve hot.

title: quesadia snacks
directions: Fold tortilla in half to crease and open.
On one side, place onion, garlic powder and cheese.
Fold in half again.
Microwave until cheese is melted.
Enjoy.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice thinly the cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Soak for 3 hours in 3 tablespoons salt and enough ice water to cover.
Drain well.
Mix together 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup vinegar and pour over drained cukes.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 days.
Put in containers and freeze.
Makes 3 pints.
Thaw and add sour cream or serve plain.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all good.
Roll out and cut out.
Bake until done.
Eat warm or cold with good, cold milk.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in order given.
Sift together next 4 ingredients; add to first.
Fold in the apples, pecans and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover warm cake with following glaze.

title: chewy cranberry squares
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light.
Add eggs and lemon juice. Beat until smooth and creamy.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Gently fold in nuts and cranberry cubes.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.
Makes 24 bars.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a bowl, whisk together mayo and sour cream. Stir in artichoke hearts, cheese and Tabasco. Spoon into an ovenproof baking dish and bake 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly. Serve with crackers or French bread slices. Makes 2 cups or 11 servings.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Heat together the soy sauce, chicken broth, sugar, brown sugar, vinegar, ginger and garlic.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight in fridge.
Bake at 325° for about 3 hours; turn several times until liquid is gone.

title: roasted garlic and pepper dip
directions: Gently peel outer skins from garlic; cut off top one-fourth of each head and discard.
Place garlic, cut side up, in center of a piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil; drizzle with olive oil.
Fold aluminum foil over garlic, sealing tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until garlic is soft.
Remove from oven; let cool completely.
Remove and discard papery skin from garlic.
Scoop out soft garlic with a spoon; set garlic aside.
Spoon yogurt onto several layers of heavy-duty paper towels; spread to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cover with additional paper towels; let stand 5 minutes.
Scrape yogurt into container of an electric blender, using a rubber spatula.

Add reserved garlic, red pepper, ground pepper, salt and onion powder; cover and process on high speed 1 minute or until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides. Spoon mixture into a serving bowl and stir in sour cream.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables or steamed shrimp.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water until tender. Add salt, black pepper and butter.
Make a thickening of flour with 1/2 cup milk. Pour into potatoes.
Stir.
Add milk until it is as thick or thin as desired. Simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
Enjoy with cornbread!

title: unmatchable fruit mix
directions: Combine fruit except banana in a large bowl and refrigerate. Combine the remaining ingredients in a small bowl and mix well. To serve, add banana to the fruit. Toss with dressing. Then serve.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Cook hamburger medium done; set aside.
Cook next 3 ingredients (celery, carrots and potatoes) in bouillon broth until tender.
Add green beans, tomatoes and onion.
When hot, add hamburger, which has been chopped up in small chunks.
Simmer all ingredients slowly for about an hour.
Makes 10 servings.

title: kraut pork pinwheel
directions: Combine
ground
pork, bread crumbs, eggs, salt, pepper and Worcestershire
sauce and mix thoroughly.
Pat mixture on waxed paper to 10 x 7-inch rectangle.
Top with sauerkraut and onion. Spread
evenly
and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place loaf
in shallow
baking dish and arrange bacon slices across top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then put French fried onion rings on top and bake for 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: waldorf salad dressing
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Fold in the remaining ingredients.
This keeps well.

title: hot cheesy beef dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels; set aside.
Chop dried beef finely.
Combine cream cheese and milk; beat on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in beef, green pepper, onion, garlic and white pepper; mix well. Stir in sour cream; spoon into a greased 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve dip hot with assorted crackers.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: stuffed cabbages
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cabbage and sausage.
Wash cabbage leaves and drain.
Steam leaves.
Divide mixture up and place small portion on each leaf.
Roll and secure with toothpick. Place a sausage on top of each roll. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Top each with 1/2 marshmallow, cut side down.
Return to oven 1 minute.
Remove from pan.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Top with chopped nuts or 1 pecan half.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion and garlic powder in Crisco until onion is clear. Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Stir to chop tomatoes.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp, crab meat and chicken; pour in chicken broth.
Cook until heated.
Serve over hot rice.

title: pam's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate 4 hours before baking.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° in greased muffin tins.
Will keep 1 week in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken. Remove all bones, skin and fat.
Cut up.
Grease casserole dish.
Mix together beans, water chestnuts and almonds. Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice to make a sauce. Stir together and heat slightly.
Put chicken mixture in dish. Pour heated
sauce over chicken mixture and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: quick pie crust
directions: Mix well and press into pie plate.

title: terrific tacos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. If using taco shells, place on baking sheet and bake for 6 minutes. If using tortillas, warm slightly.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar.
Beat well.
Add cheese, corn and 3/4 of the bacon.
Turn mixture into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with remaining bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread one box of dry cake mix over filling (I use white cake mix).
Drizzle melted margarine or butter over this.
Top with coconut or nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fritos dip
directions: Chop green onions.
Mix onions with other ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with Fritos.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add all ingredients except cheese.
Put in a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli
according
to package.
Mix crackers in melted butter.
Put part of crackers on bottom of baking dish. Layer with
broccoli
and
as much cheese as you want.
Cover with remaining crackers.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: layered blackberry dessert
directions: Combine 3/4 cup blackberries and sugar in container of an electric blender; top with cover and process until smooth.
Press puree through a sieve to remove seeds.
Combine yogurt and extract; stir.
Layer blackberry mixture and yogurt mixture evenly in 2 (6 ounce) parfait glasses.
If desired, garnish with blackberries and mint.

title: gingernuts
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Stir in eggs, vinegar and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Mix all together well and shape into small balls about the size of small walnuts.
(Use flour on fingertips.)
Bake on greased cookie sheet 10-12 minutes at 325° or 350° oven.
Makes 5 dozen, plus.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook first three ingredients until turning brown in color, about 12 to 15 minutes, over medium heat.
Pour in buttered 8 x 8 pan.
Place Hershey chocolate bars over top of mixture until melted and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts or pecans.

title: date pudding
directions: Pour water and soda over dates and cool.
Set aside.
Mix next 6 ingredients.
Add cooled dates (do not drain) to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Break the cake in pieces.
Place one layer in bowl, then Butterscotch Sauce, whipped cream and bananas.
Repeat layers and end with whipped cream.
Decorate with bananas.

title: shrimp salad dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: aunt estelle's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in brown sugar.
Pour mixture into 13 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add enough bread cubes and press into mixture to fill dish well and absorb liquid well.
Scatter raisins over mixture and press in with fork. Place baking dish in shallow pan.
Pour hot water into larger pan, 1 inch deep.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Chop onion and bell pepper; saute in butter.
Mix soups, tomatoes and rice.
Add vegetables and shrimp last.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: cinnamon sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until light and fluffy. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll in small balls onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: salmon pasta skillet
directions: In a large skillet, bring chicken broth to boiling.
Add pasta and vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, until pasta is tender.
Stir in cream cheese until combined.
Stir in milk, Parmesan cheese, basil and a dash of pepper.
Gently stir in salmon.
Cook until heated through.

title: plantation cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Mix eggs, oil, buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg mixture and beat.
Add boiling water and mix well (batter will be very thin).
Bake in a Pyrex pan for 30 minutes.
Immediately cover with topping; broil until bubbly. Watch carefully; topping burns easily.

title: dewberry cobbler
directions: Put dewberries, sugar and
oleo
in large pan and bring to a rolling boil.
Take biscuits out of can and roll each one as thin as possible.
Will	need
some flour to roll biscuits. When rolled, cut into very thin	strips	and
add
them to the boiling mixture and cook
the dough until very tender.
Should be done in 15 to 20
minutes.	Very
good
served hot with ice cream.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Place apples in buttered 10 x 6 x 3/4 inch baking dish. Sprinkle gelatin over apples.
Combine flour and sugar in small bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yield:
4-6 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease casserole.
Mix ingredients and pour into casserole. Place casserole into pan of hot water.
Bake in 350° oven.
Top with sauce.

title: foolproof pastry
directions: Add shortening to flour, salt, sugar and mix until the consistency of coarse meal.
Add water beaten egg, vinegar and blend lightly.
Shape into a ball.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours.
Divide equally.
Roll thin and place on two 10-inch pie plates.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° for baked shell recipes or unbaked according to particular recipe.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Melt chips & morsels together in double boiler.
Add pecans. Drop by spoon onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: slush
directions: Make in gallon container and freeze.
Spoon out and serve with grapefruit pop.

title: rhubarb sauce for ham or lamb
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cook, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Discard cinnamon stick.
Use over meat.

title: meat and vegetable casserole dish
directions: Mix creamed corn, crumbled bread, egg and milk and put in dish.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain and put on top of corn mixture.
Fix instant mashed potatoes and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes brown on top.
Good with a side salad.

title: macaroni-tuna casserole
directions: Blend butter and flour in saucepan.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings and next 3 ingredients.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Place macaroni in casserole.
Pour creamed tuna over top; mix well.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; wash and set caps aside.
Chop stems and saute in butter.
Add onion and saute until browned.
In a bowl, mix the mushroom-onion mixture and all remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Spoon into mushroom caps, mounding slightly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Combine artichokes, cheeses, mayonnaise, garlic and onion.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: chow-chow relish(heritage recipe)
directions: Combine chopped vegetables, sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 4 to 6 hours in a cool place.
Drain well.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Wash broccoli; separate flowerets and coarsely chop stalk. Bring water to a boil; add salt and broccoli.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Combine soup and next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Fold in broccoli; pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine stuffing mix and butter; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grate carrots; set aside.
Mix other ingredients; then add carrots.
Blend well, pour in greased cake pans.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dilute lemonade according to directions on can.
Stir in strawberries.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice. Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: cherry refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and beat well. Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Add nuts and cherries.
Stir to blend.
Shape into rolls of 1 1/2-inches.
Roll in wax paper and refrigerate.
Chill well.
Slice into 1-inch slices.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: bacon cheese dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing. Mix until well blended. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill. Serve with crackers or rye bread rounds.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill to serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and add buttermilk as needed.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients, except tortillas and cheese.
In a 13 x 9-inch casserole, alternate tortillas with meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover the last 10 minutes.

title: swirl pie
directions: Mix well the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and milk.
Add almond extract, Amaretto and Cool Whip.
Fold in 1/2 can pie filling.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in floured 9 X 13 pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line baking sheet with foil.
Spray with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine potatoes, oil, tomato paste, vinegar, chili powder and salt.
Toss well to thoroughly coat.
Arrange potatoes in a single layer on baking sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together over low heat.
Good with beef, chicken or pork.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in 1 1/2-quarts water with salt, onion, carrot and celery.
Cook until tender, 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Strip meat from chicken in large strips.
Cool chicken and broth, then refrigerate. Combine remaining ingredients with 1/2 cup broth, mixing until smooth.
Heat 3 cups broth in skillet.
Add flour mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring continually.
Add chicken and blend well. Line a 9-inch deep dish pan with crust.
Fill; add top crust.
Vent top and flute edges.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple mince muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 18 muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir only until all ingredients are blended.
Spoon equal portions into prepared muffin cups.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from muffin cups; top with apple-cinnamon glaze.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and eggs until smooth.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix in flour, then add coconut and pineapple.
Pour into greased pie pans.
Don't flour the pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin pans.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: 7-layer casserole
directions: Use a 2-quart baking dish with tight-fitting lid.
Line bottom of dish with rice, then layer with corn.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce over.
Add 1/2 can (tomato sauce can) water; pour over.
Spread onion and green pepper over sauce.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie pan.
Cook beef in skillet.
Put in bottom of pan with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese over meat. Stir together Bisquick, eggs and milk.
Pour over top of meat. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: hot crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix ingredients together; top-sprinkle Cheddar cheese and some paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers. (This recipe can be made in advance.)

title: broccoli bake
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Layer half of broccoli, half of soup mixture and half can of onions in a 10 x 6-inch pan.
Top with remaining broccoli and soup mixture.

title: fantasy fudge
