directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan; bring to a full rolling boil over medium heat. Continue boiling for 5 minutes, stirring continually to prevent scorching. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate or peanut butter pieces until melted. Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; mix until well blended. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 pan. Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares. Yields 3 pounds.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Makes a large amount.

title: cornish pasties
directions: Sift flour with salt.
Rub in margarine mixed to a stiff dough with little cold water.
Divide pastry into four.
Roll out into 7-inch rounds.
Peel large potato and cut into small cubes.
Chop finely 1 small onion.
Mix potato and onion with beef.
Divide mixture into four; place in center of pastry rounds.
Moisten pastry edge.
Join pastry edges together, joining at center and sealing down each side.
Crimp edges so moisture does not escape. Brush the pastry with little milk or beaten egg.
Bake in center of oven at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 50 minutes, until golden brown.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine butter, water and cocoa in saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Stir occasionally.
Add flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Spread on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. While cake is baking, make frosting.
Frost while hot.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine the ingredients with enough salad dressing, regular or fat-free may be used, to make of a desired consistency.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugars, eggs, oil, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir in nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Spray with Pam.
Stir with spoon.

title: grandma tripp's kale soup
directions: Cook kidney beans, linguica and chourico together about 2 hours.
Add onions, potatoes, kale and salt and pepper.
Cook all until done, about an hour or so.
Serve with saltines.
Delicious. Even better second day.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain, rinse and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate at least 3 hours. Enjoy!

title: mom's english pea-asparagus casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
Put asparagus in baking dish.
Cover with peas.
Dot with a few pats of butter.
Sprinkle with salt.
Spoon out soup and cover top.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° to 400° until bubbly and cheese is melted and slightly browned. Can make ahead and bake when needed.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up vegetables. Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all together (Jell-O, dry).

title: max hustak's pasta salad
directions: Marinate the vermicelli in the Accent, seasoning salt, lemon juice and olive oil 2 hours. Stir occasionally during the second hour. Then add the peppers, onion, pimentos, black olives and celery. Stir in the Miracle Whip salad dressing. Stir well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: nacho dip
directions: In pie plate, place cream cheese evenly.
Top with salsa, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes until cheese melts. Serve with nacho chips.

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening in 4 quart saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.	Let cool.
Add sugar, molasses, and egg.
Beat well. Add remaining dry ingredients.
Chill. Form 1 inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake in 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: holland salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Combine oil, vinegar and mayonnaise. Add to meat mixture; mix well.
Garnish with mayonnaise, sliced, hard-cooked eggs and shredded pickled beets.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef in sherry
directions: Cut up beef into 1-inch cubes and brown.
Put in large casserole dish.
Add soup, mushrooms and sherry.
Mix; cover and bake approximately 3 hours at 325° or 4 hours at 300°.
Serve over rice.

title: moros(dominican republic style)
directions: Cook locrio (basic yellow rice), substituting beans for meat. Instead of plain water use liquid from the beans.

title: red velvet cake
directions: You will also need 4 lined, greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into casserole dish, cover and bake at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in casserole.
Add boiled tomatoes, oregano and water.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes, until brown.

title: crisp onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place all ingredients, except potatoes, in a gallon bag.
Mix well.
Put in potatoes and shake until they are well coated.
Bake 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: pretzel fruit top torte
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan for 8 minutes in 400° oven.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip and spread on pretzel layer.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen fruit.
Chill until thickened.
Spoon onto cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Stir in cereal and stir to coat, work quickly.
Put hot mixture into wax paper lined pan or well-greased pan.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Boil tortellini; drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight.
Take out at least 2 hours before serving. Makes a lot!

title: peanut butter gems
directions: Mix in bowl peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and powdered sugar until blended together.
Melt the chocolate chips, then use a cookie sheet and spread the peanut butter mixture out on the cookie sheet.
Pour melted chocolate chips on top and spread over mixture.
Put in freezer for at least 3 hours, then use a knife to cut into pieces.
Always serve cold. If they get warm, they become mushy and not as good.
So always keep in freezer until ready to serve.
Enjoy!

title: cheese pudding
directions: Trim bread and dice.
Put in glass dish and pour melted butter over.
Add cheese and stir.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over bread.
Stir lightly.
Beat egg whites and pat on top. Cook at 325° to 350° (ovens vary) until brown on top.

title: johnny bakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl, then rub in the fat until mixture resembles breadcrumbs.
Pour milk in and stir to make soft dough.
Knead on floured board, then refrigerate for 30 minutes. Break dough into lemon-sized pieces, roll into balls and flatten to 1/2 inch or 1 centimeter thickness.
Fry these in hot oil until golden or bake in hot oven, gas mark 7,425° or 220° Celsius.
While still hot, tear bakes open and butter generously.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: old time tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, butter, soda and vanilla. Add flour until mixture is thick. Roll out mixture and cut cookies. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons of oleo.
Combine potatoes, cheese, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper with onions.
Place in greased casserole dish (13 x 2-inch).
Crush corn flakes and mix with melted oleo.
Place on top of mixture.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: layered cheese dome
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese and lemon juice until fluffy.
Divide into 2 portions.
To one portion, stir in Parmesan cheese and chili sauce.
Turn into lightly oiled 2 1/2 or 3 cup mold.
To remaining cream cheese add cottage cheese, onion salt and garlic powder, beat until nearly smooth.
Stir in parsley, bell pepper or celery.
Spoon atop first layer in mold.
Cover and chill.
Unmold.

title: danny's fish fry
directions: Blend in a blender to make a powder. Coat fish and fry in hot oil. M-mmmm!

title: sue's cherry cream pie
directions: Mix the ingredients together and add 1 cup Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells.
Put cherry pie filling on top. Makes 2 pies.

title: one bowl buttercream frosting
directions: Beat butter, add powdered sugar, cocoa alternately with milk, beating to spreading consistency.
Add Vanilla.
Stir.

title: frozen cupcakes
directions: Combine chocolate wafer crumbs and butter until well mixed. Spoon 1 tablespoon of crumbs into 12 foil muffin cups.
Press firmly.
Set aside remaining crumbs.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in 1/2 cup milk. Combine moistened crumbs with beef, pork, egg, salt, pepper and allspice. Cook onion in butter until tender and add to meat mixture. Beat the mixture while slowly adding remaining lukewarm milk. Chill mixture until firm. Roll into appetizer size meatballs. Heat clarified butter in skillet. Add meatballs and fry until cooked through. Drain, then dust meatballs lightly with flour. Add milk and broth for gravy and simmer for a few minutes. Adjust seasoning. Serves 6.

title: baked green beans
directions: Mix beans, vinegar, sugar and onion. Bake in casserole dish covered with foil for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and bake, uncovered, for another 30 minutes.

title: apple-pear coffee cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream stick of butter and sugar. Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients, alternately with sour cream.
Fold in chopped apples and pears. Spread in pan.

title: quick sauerkraut
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cover partially and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for about 45 minutes. Add small amount of water, if necessary, to prevent scorching.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add egg and applesauce. Sift in dry ingredients adding raisins and nuts.
Mix together and stir well.
Drop by spoon on well-oiled cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pepper steak
directions: Put butter and garlic powder in a skillet.
Add meat and brown. Remove meat and add green pepper and onions.
Saute for 2 or 3 minutes, then put meat back in skillet.
Add tomatoes, soy sauce and bouillon cube.
Simmer (covered) until meat is tender; approximately 45 minutes.
Mix water, flour and sugar together and add to meat mixture.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: cherry and cashew nut candy
directions: Chop chocolate and shortening and melt in top of double boiler.
Add coffee.
Put a thin layer of this mixture on the bottom of a greased square pan, lined with paper.
Sprinkle with cherries, cashew nuts and coconut.
Cover with remaining chocolate mixture.
Chill in the refrigerator until firm and cut in squares. Yields about 24.

title: microwave spicy turkey roast
directions: Remove mesh from thawed turkey.
Lay turkey out as flat as possible on a cutting board, placing the skin side down.
Combine garlic, rosemary, pepper and salt in the work bowl of the food processor with the steel blade in place, or in blender.
Turn motor on.
Add the oil, processing until coarsely chopped.
Spread half the garlic mixture over the inside of the turkey.
Reroll the turkey.
Spread outside of roll with remaining garlic mixture. Wrap firmly in microsafe plastic film.
Secure firmly with string. Pierce film in two or three places with fork.
Place on microsafe cooking rack over microsafe roasting pan.
Microwave at High power for 10 minutes.
Turn roast over.
Microwave at Medium power for 35 to 40 minutes, turning roast 2 or 3 times while cooking, until roast registers 170° in several places (use instant reading thermometer to check temperature).
Thicken pan juices for gravy, if desired.
Remove from oven.
Let stand, covered, for 15 minutes. Cut thin slices to serve.
Garnish with orange slices and rosemary, if desired.

title: pickled beans and corn
directions: String and break beans; cook until beans are soft enough to mash; drain.
Put in gallon jar or crock and add 1/2 cup pickling salt.
Cover with cold water.
Weight down with something heavy enough to keep beans under water.
Let set for 8 to 10 days.
Boil corn on cob.
Pickle in jar using same amount of salt and water. Drain; after 8 to 10 days, cut corn off cob and mix with beans. Heat beans and corn mixture until hot all the way through.
Pack in hot jars and seal.
Process in canner in boiling water 15 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Presoak beans for faster cooking.
Combine ingredients; cook in heavy pot over low heat until tender, at least 2 hours.
Mash with potato masher until beans blend into soup.
Best served with warm corn bread.

title: ham loaves
directions: Saute the celery and onion in butter.
Combine all ingredients together and form into small loaves.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Drain the excess fat.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, then add frozen orange juice. Dissolve; set aside.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water and sugar; stir.
Pour this into orange mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thick, then turn heat to simmer and let bubble for awhile.
Pour into a bowl; let set up in fridge, then whip until smooth.
Whip whipping cream.
Fold into orange mixture, then add 2 or 3 bananas, 2 cans mandarin oranges (drained) and 1 can crushed pineapple (drained).
Serves 20 to 25.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Steam or cook the spinach as directed on package.
Add the margarine, cream cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: meat roll-ups
directions: Chop green part of onions fine.
Mix with cream cheese.
Have 1 slice of meat; put cream cheese mixture along edge of meat. Start rolling one side of meat until it is in a log roll shape. Repeat process until finished.
Chill overnight.
These are really delicious.

title: stir-fry cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain.
Chop onion and put in drippings.
Cook slowly until clear.
Chop cabbage and add to drippings.
Add water.
Cook, covered, stirring frequently.
Then, when done, crumble bacon over top.
Serve warm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk gradually.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 1 minute or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken and vegetables; spoon into pastry-lined dish.
Top with remaining pastry.
Seal edges; cut vents.
Bake for 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: rice-vermicelli pilaf
directions: Break pasta into bite-sized pieces.
Saute in margarine in skillet over medium heat until light brown.
Add rice, bouillon cubes and water to cover.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: bubble bread
directions: Place dough balls in Bundt cake pan.
Melt butter and pour over dough balls.
Mix brown sugar, pudding and pecans.
Sprinkle mixture over dough balls.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Let rise overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Slice and arrange layer of bananas evenly over the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Prepare lemon gelatin according to directions on package; pour over bananas.
Chill in the refrigerator until solid (about 1 hour).

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Mix oleo and flour together and cook about 1 minute.
Add all spices and hot pepper, then the milk last.
Add the cheese.
Cook in double boiler until begins to thicken.
Serve hot with Fritos or Doritos.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup margarine. Place in casserole dish. Mix
brown sugar, flour, pecans and 1/3 cup margarine. Crumble on top of sweet potato mixture. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts and coconut in bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over nuts and coconut. Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar. Spoon on top of cake. Bake for approximately 30 to 45 minutes at 350°. Cake will crack and icing will go to bottom.

title: rigatoni
directions: Mix together the tomato paste, tomato sauce and Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies.
Mix together the garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Boil noodles and onion for 20 minutes.
While noodles and onion boil, brown beef seasoned with garlic salt, Worcestershire and oregano mixture.
Pour noodles and onion into a deep dish casserole.
Spread meat mixture on top of noodles.
Pour sauce mixture over meat.
Slice Velveeta cheese 1/4-inch thick and layer on top of entire casserole.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: russian tea ii
directions: Mix and use as needed.
Stores well in airtight covered container.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes.
Cook in pan with vegetable cooking spray.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Drain juice from peach halves into kettle.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add peaches and cook for 5 minutes, or until peaches are heated through.
Remove spice bags. Pack peaches in hot, sterilized jars.
Fill jars with boiling syrup.
Seal.
Makes three 8 oz. jars.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure dry ingredients into large bowl. Stir.
Grease two bread pans.
Beat egg, juice, milk and oil.
Stir into flour mixture until blended.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix all together; slice rolls.
Fill.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baked french fries
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut lengthwise into 3/8-inch slices.
Toss potatoes with ingredients in bowl.
Place potatoes single layer on greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Turn over and bake 10 minutes longer or until crisp and tender.
Serves 4.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover and chill to blend flavors.
Serve over tossed salad greens, sliced tomatoes or head lettuce salad. Makes 2 cups.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9-inch loaf pan. Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda in a large bowl and mix well.
Blend oil and eggs into strawberries.
Add to flour mixture.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes. Let cool in pan on a rack 10 minutes.
Turn loaf out onto rack and cool completely.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in 1/4 cup soy sauce and seasoning salt for several hours.
Heat wok or frying pan and 1 tablespoon of oil. Fry chicken until done.
Remove chicken.
Heat another tablespoon of oil.
Stir-fry broccoli, bok choy, mushrooms, bamboo and chestnuts.
Add 1/4 cup soy sauce while cooking; cook until tender.
Add chicken and thicken with a mixture of 1 tablespoon cornstarch, 1 cup water and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Add cashews. Serve over rice.

title: coconut cream pie (makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in double boiler until thick. Beat egg whites well and pour into batter after it is done.
Beat with mixer.
Put coconut in batter; add vanilla and a little salt.
Toast a little coconut in oven.
Let cool.
Put Cool Whip on top of pies and sprinkle toasted coconut on top of Cool Whip.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat 2 minutes stirring constantly.
Add milk.
Keep stirring until mixture boils.
Remove from heat; cool.
Add confectioners sugar beating well after each addition until thick enough to spread. Enough to fill and frost an 8 or 9-inch layer cake. Good on spice cake.

title: old-fashioned shortcake
directions: Put egg and melted butter in measuring cup; add milk to make 1 cup.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Superb with strawberries.

title: chicken and creamy rice casserole
directions: Put rice, water and soup in baking dish.
Add onion soup mix. Put chicken on top of mixture.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pioneer beans
directions: Brown
meat, bacon and onions together.
Add the 3 cans of beans,
mix, and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add balance of ingredients and bake for 80 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crunch
directions: Cook apples, sugar, cinnamon and water until slightly tender. Pour in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs that you have mixed with melted margarine.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes.

title: beet jelly(that tastes just like grape jelly)
directions: Boil beets; cut up so they bleed (throw away beets and keep juice, 4 cups).
Boil beet juice and ReaLemon juice.
Add 1 package pectin; boil 1 minute.
Add sugar and grape jello.
Return to hard boil for 3 1/2 minutes.
Put in jars and seal with wax.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling; mix.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
When mixture is set, spread with remaining ingredients.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water together.
With a fork, add cranberries and rest of the ingredients.
Put in a mold and let set overnight.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix all this well (use only fruit from fruit cocktail) and let set overnight.
Slice to serve.
Beautiful to look at and a treat to eat.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Grate the cheese and place it in a mixer bowl.
Add the pimientos and cream cheese.
Mix at a slow speed.
Slowly add the Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise.
After the mixture is consistent, increase the speed of the mixer until the consistency is smooth. Yield: 5 to 6 cups.

title: beet salad
directions: Place beets in one quart bowl.
Add mixture of remaining ingredients.
toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate one or two days.
turn beets occasionally.
Serve beets with some of the marinade.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: favorite corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, eggs and shortening.
Beat for 1 minute. Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bread is golden brown and tests done. Yield:
9 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 2-quart dish, mix sugar and Karo syrup.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Cook on High 3 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Add soda and stir well.
Pour into a well-buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool for 1 hour and then break into small pieces.

title: chicken linguini
directions: Dice chicken, then saute chicken in butter with Lea & Perrins, bell pepper, onion and spices until light brown.
Add cream of mushroom soup, broccoli cheese soup, 1/2 can milk and 1/2 can water.
Let simmer about 30 minutes.
Cook your noodles in separate pot.
Then either pour sauce over noodles or drain and mix sauce and noodles together.
Serve with hot bread and salad.

title: french mustard sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until thickened. Great to spread on chicken before grilling.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with the sugar, salt, corn syrup and butter.
Add 1 cup of pecans and pour into 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: turkey gobble
directions: Crumble raw turkey in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer croutons on top.
In separate bowl, mix soup, celery, onion and water.
Pour over turkey and croutons.
Put cheese on top, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Wash the cauliflower and broccoli and separate into small flowerets, finely chop the green onions.
Combine the mayonnaise and the envelope of buttermilk dressing mix; add the sugar and vinegar and blend well.
Toss the vegetables with the dressing and marinate overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: easy tortilla dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order as listed in a shallow casserole dish.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Roll out on floured board until thin; cut into small squares. Keep your broth hot.
Drop dumplings into broth; use a large spoon and keep them pushed back.
Do Not Stir.
Cover and simmer until done.
Add cool cooked chicken.
Best around.

title: italian beef
directions: Roast beef at 325°, uncovered, until rare.
Cool and slice thinly.
To pan drippings, add rest of ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Add sliced beef and simmer for 5 hours.
Serve on buns or sliced French bread.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, shortening and milk to make crust and roll out in small amounts.
Pare and core apples.
Place apple on crust.
In apple center, sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and a dot of butter.
Mold crust around apple.
Combine sugar, water, cinnamon, food coloring and margarine; bring to boiling.
Pour over apple dumplings which have been placed 1 inch apart in ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes or until apples are done.
They may be basted occasionally.
Serve warm with cream, ice cream or whipped topping.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull berries.
Mix 1/2 of them with cornstarch and water.
Crush.
Add lemon juice, salt and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens, approximately 5 minutes.
Cool.
Pour remaining berries into crust.
Cover with cooked mixture.
Cool.
Spread whipped cream on top.
Enjoy!

title: banana milk shakes
directions: Stir together 1/2 cup milk, eggs and a banana until thoroughly mixed.
Add remaining milk, cracked ice and vanilla.
Beat with a rotary beater.
Serve.

title: onion rings
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk.
Add dry ingredients; beat well.
Peel onion.
Slice and break into rings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix salsa and soup together.

Fill shells with chicken, Cheddar cheese and a heaping spoonful of salsa mix. Roll shells and arrange in cake pan or casserole dish. Pour remaining salsa mix over top and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake until cheese is melted on top.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Thaw 3 to 4 hours then, just before serving, cover with 1 liter of ginger ale or Sprite or Seven-Up.
One batch will serve about 30 people.
Use food coloring, if desired.
A three gallon ice cream pail works great for freezing.
Can keep frozen for 3 to 6 months.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Saute onion in butter, but not too brown. Mix all ingredients together and place into ungreased casserole. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 16.

title: parmesan corn on the cob
directions: In a bowl, combine the butter, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning; set aside.
Remove husks and silk from corn; place in a shallow microwave safe dish.
Add water.
Cover and microwave on high for 10 to 13 minutes, turning once.
Let stand for 5 minutes; drain.
Brush with butter mixture; sprinkle with salt.
Serves 4.

title: punch(serves 90)
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
This may be frozen and used when needed.
Add the ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: hot asparagus bowl
directions: Combine lemon juice, butter, Worcestershire, salt and pepper. Add juice from asparagus.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Pour over asparagus.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter in a double boiler; then mix with corn and green chilies.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: low calorie french fries
directions: Stir potatoes in egg whites and spice.
Spray a cookie sheet with vegetable oil.
Place potatoes on cookie sheet and bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Stir potatoes about every 8 minutes. Eat immediately.

title: almond shortbread cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add almond extract, then add flour.
Roll out; cut cookies.
Heat oven to 350°; bake for 8 to 10 minutes, brown on bottom only.

title: dean's yuky popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn hot and crisp in slow oven (300° to 325°). Combine sugar, water, salt, corn syrup and vinegar.
Cook to hard ball stage at 250°.
Add vanilla.
Pour slowly over popcorn, mix well to coat every kernel.
Press into balls (12 to 15).

title: holiday ham sauce
directions: Mix together sugar, dry mustard and salt over double boiler. Gradually add the rest of the ingredients. Cook for 1/2 hour or until thick.

title: pumpkin dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add combined oats and flour; mix well.
Spread evenly onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool slightly.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt and sharp Cheddar cheese.
Put into greased 9 x 9-inch dish (2-quart) with macaroni.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs for the last 5 minutes, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli, cauliflower and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, add broccoli and cauliflower.
Pour mixture over vegetables.
Top with remaining cheese; cover loosely with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put uncooked rice in bottom of oblong casserole dish and put chicken pieces on top of rice.
Mix soup with water and onion soup mix and pour over chicken and rice.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour 45 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: In saucepan mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add vinegar and water. Boil 5 minutes, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Add beets and simmer until beets are hot.
Add butter and stir.

title: macedoine of fruits
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes. Chill.
Add brandy, liqueur and fruit. Cover and chill 2 hours. Serve
with main course or as a dessert. Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and vanilla in medium mixing bowl. Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: world's best cookies
directions: In a large bowl cream together butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg, mixing well.
Then add oil.
Mix well.
Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well and form into balls the size of small walnuts. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Allow to cool on cookie sheet for a few minutes before removing.
Yields approximately 8 dozen cookies.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix ingredients.
Alternate layers:
vanilla wafers, bananas and mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: lemon glazed bread
directions: Blend well butter and 1 cup sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla, then add dry ingredients with milk, lemon rind and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
While bread bakes, in small bowl, stir 1/4 cup sugar and juice of 1 lemon.
Pour this on hot bread.
Cool well before slicing.
Better second day.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Pour into cupcake papers.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cod steaks with cheddar cheese
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice together and set aside.
Grease rack in broiling pan.
Place cod steaks on rack; broil 5 to 7 minutes until fish flakes easily.
Remove pan; do not turn fish.
Spread cheese mixture on fish.
Return pan to broiler; broil 1 minute longer or until topping is lightly browned and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Mix ingredients; stir and let set for 5 minutes.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; let set for 20 minutes.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat shortening, brown sugar, water and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in chips.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: pistachio salad(watergate salad)
directions: Mix together pudding and pineapple (undrained).
Add food coloring until a medium green.
Add cottage cheese and nuts. Gently fold in mandarin oranges.
Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with red and green decorating sugar and serve.
Makes approximately 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy spinach dip in bread bowl
directions: Combine sour cream, mayo and seasoning in bowl.
Stir in onions, spinach, water chestnuts and red pepper.
Cover and refrigerate until set.

title: green beans in herb butter
directions: Place beans in electric skillet or stove top skillet. Over medium heat, melt butter over beans.
Add onion, garlic, celery and sesame seed.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Toss beans and sauce several times before serving.

title: green bean puff
directions: Combine green beans and celery in 5 cup casserole.
Mix together mayonnaise, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Gradually add the milk.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Fold into mayonnaise mixture and pile lightly on top of beans.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, until sauce puffs and browns.

title: sliced apple dip
directions: Slice red and yellow apples into a bowl.
Cover with pineapple juice.
Soak overnight.

title: creamed chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in a baking dish and cover with chopped nuts.
Cover dish and bake at low heat for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbling.
Can be made ahead of time and baked when needed.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple; reserve juice.
Add 2 cups of sugar and 3 tablespoons of flour.
Cook until thickened.
Add egg yolks; cook 2 minutes longer, stirring often.
Let cool completely.
Cook acini de pepe macaroni about 8 minutes.
Rinse and drain completely.
Pour thickened juice over macaroni; let set overnight.
Add all fruit, marshmallows and Cool Whip; fold to mix.
This is great for potlucks or picnics.
Freezes well, also!

title: sweet butternut casserole
directions: Peel squash; cut in half lengthwise and remove seeds and membranes.
Cook squash, covered, in salted water 25 minutes, until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add sugar, spices and butter to squash.
Beat on medium speed of mixer 1 minute or until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla; beat an additional 30 seconds.
Pour into a lightly greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Garnish with pecan halves.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk. Mix with electric mixer.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir well.
Add zucchini.
Pour batter in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Put chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: carrot & raisin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to eat. It's best to make ahead so raisins and soften.

title: mary's yummy rice
directions: Follow package directions to prepare cooked rice, adding chicken bouillon cubes to water.
Saute minced onion in butter until onion is soft and golden.
Remove from heat and stir in parsley and oregano.
Add cooked rice and mix gently over warm heat.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan or Romano cheese (grated) and mix in.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add pumpkin and mix.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Add the soda, flour and chocolate chips.
Grease pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In large casserole dish, microwave broccoli in 1/2 cup of water for 5 minutes.
Spread evenly over bottom of dish.
Dilute soup with 1 soup can of water and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle grated cheese over soup (if desired, 1 to 1 1/2 cups cooked, cubed chicken or turkey may be added at this time).
Spread dry dressing mix over casserole and sprinkle with 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rice goulash
directions: Brown hamburger, adding diced green pepper and onion.
Drain off any fat.
Add Rice-A-Roni and hot water.
Stir frequently. When it starts to boil, turn down heat to low and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add your favorite vegetable on the side and eat.

title: barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Put meat in pan. Add sauce. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 1/4 hours. Baste frequently if too dry. Turn oven to 425° last few minutes to brown. Makes enough sauce for 2 or 3 chickens that are cut up.

title: broccoli with pine nuts and raisins
directions: Cut the broccoli into florets. Trim and peel the stalks and cut into dime-size pieces. In a medium skillet, heat the oil with the pepper flakes and garlic. Add the pine nuts and raisins; saute until the nuts begin to color, about 2 minutes. Add the broccoli and saute until tender, about 5 minutes. Add the tomatoes and cook until just heated through, about 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and set aside.
Let cool completely.
In large bowl, mix yeast, warm water and beaten eggs. Then mix all together.
Add plain flour last.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: pat-a-pie oil pastry(heartwise)
directions: Into an 8 or 9-inch pie plate, sift together flour, sugar and salt.
With fork, whip together salad oil and milk; pour over flour mixture.
Mix with fork until all flour is dampened.
Reserve about 1/3 of dough for top "crust."
Press remaining dough evenly against bottom and sides of pie plate.
Fill with fruit filling.
For top "crust" crumble reserved dough.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake as directed in fruit pie recipe.

title: best ever chocolate cake
directions: Heat 2 sticks butter, German's chocolate, 2 tablespoons cocoa and water to rolling boil.	Cool slightly.	Pour mixture over sugar, flour, eggs, buttermilk, soda and salt.
Blend and bake in 9
1/2 x 13-inch greased pan at 325° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage until not pink.
Drain well.
Cool completely. Add all other ingredients and mix until well blended.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: frozen rainbow delight
directions: Beat whipping cream until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until soft peaks form.
Fold in macaroon crumbs, pecans and vanilla. Spread half of the macaroon mixture in bottom of a two-piece, 10-inch tube pan.
Spread raspberry sherbet evenly over macaroon mixture.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Repeat with other sherbets, freezing 30 minutes between layers.
Top with remaining macaroon mixture and freeze until firm.
Let frozen dessert stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.
Remove side piece of tube pan.
Slice. Yields 16 servings.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Mix.
Dip spoon first in hot liquid (prevents dough from sticking to spoon).
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling water to which 1 tablespoon oil and 1 teaspoon salt have been added.
Cook about 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients together; mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: kentucky oven fried chicken
directions: Mix together flour, soup mix, dressing mix, paprika and salt.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and season with spices to taste. Add rest of ingredients except cheese. Stir. Simmer for 15 minutes. Top with cheese.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Do not salt.
Pick off bone; save broth.
Melt margarine; stir in dressing.
In a greased casserole dish, put a layer of dressing crumbs and layer of chicken.
Next, put a can of mushroom soup diluted with chicken broth.
Add another layer of crumbs, then more chicken.
Then the can of cream of chicken with equal broth.
Top with crumbs.
Serves 6.

title: secret hot dog sauce
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain fat.
Add other ingredients. Cook 1 hour.
Serve on hot dogs.

title: orange slice fruit cake
directions: Combine 1 cup orange juice and 2 cups brown sugar and pour over hot cake.
Let cool.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, melted margarine, milk, vanilla, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and the nutmeg.
Put into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix together the flour, brown sugar, pecans and 1/2 cup melted margarine; spread over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until topping has browned.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: potato skins
directions: Next time you have the urge for something crispy and delicious, try this low-calorie snack.

title: chili
directions: Place cooking oil in large pot or Dutch oven and add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is translucent.
Add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour. Garnish with Cheddar or Monterey Jack cheese and sour cream. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: good breakfast casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan, layer the bread, cheese and sausage.
Mix eggs, milk and dry mustard together.
Pour over layered ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, mix mushroom soup with milk.
Pour over the refrigerated mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: plum pudding
directions: Beat eggs light.
Add sugar, flour, soda, spices, milk, bread crumbs and suet.
Flour fruit mix.
Add to batter.
Bake in a steam pan for 3 hours with room to rise at 300°.
Decorate with blanched almonds and glazed fruit.
Serve with sugar saturated in lemon extract and lighted.
Top with whipped cream.

title: good big meat balls
directions: Mix all together and make into loose 2-inch balls (12 to 15 balls).
Put in casserole (9 x 13-inch) pan.

title: hot barbecued chicken wings
directions: Remove tips from wings and discard.
Cut wings in half.
Dust in mixture of flour and chili powder.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Heat together the sauce and hot sauce, then add chicken wings and simmer for a few minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix first three ingredients (butter, syrup and sugar).
Bring to a boil in pan for 6 minutes.
Take off heat.
Pour salt, soda and cream of tartar in at same time.
Stir until foamy.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix and spread on cookie sheet or roast pan.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir occasionally.
Pour out on brown paper bag. Let cool.
Put in airtight container.

title: avocado appetizer
directions: Mash avocados; add salt, pepper, lemon juice, chicken and mayonnaise.
Blend with fork.
Can also be done in blender or food processor.
Spread on bread halves.
Can also use tortilla chips, crackers or toasted bread.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add corn and cornbread mix; gently mix with fork.
Add eggs; mix with fork. Drop sour cream by tablespoons in different areas on top of corn mixture.
Fold in gently.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until mixture is firm.
Let cool slightly before cutting into squares.
Also good served at room temperature.
Serves 12.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients by hand; do not beat too much, just until all ingredients are moist.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pan 1 hour.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in oil in saucepan; add garlic and onion.
Saute until meat is no longer pink, approximately 10 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce and parsley; cook 15 to 20 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta, Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Spread 1 cup meat sauce in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer 1/4 of noodles and 1/3 of meat sauce; repeat 2 times.
Top with cheese and meat sauce.
Cover and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: old fashioned vanilla ice cream
directions: Put egg, half and half, sugar and vanilla in blender.
Blend on medium speed until mixture is smooth and sugar is dissolved. Slowly add the cream and continue blending on low speed until mixture is smooth, about 30 seconds.
Transfer the mixture to your machine and freeze according to manufacture's instructions.
Makes slightly more than 1 quart.

title: seeded parmesan pull-aparts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In oven, melt margarine in 8-inch or 9-inch round cake pan, tilting pan to cover.
Sprinkle seeds evenly.
Separate biscuits and cut in quarters.
Place biscuits, cheese and onion in plastic bag; shake to coat.
Place coated biscuits in pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese (in bag) on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Turn out onto serving plate immediately.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and cocoa. Heat margarine and Coke to boiling point. Pour over flour mixture. Add milk, baking soda, eggs and vanilla. Add marshmallows last. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Ice while hot.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl in order written. Place in a large baking dish with a cover.
Preheat oven to 350° and turn back to 325°.
Cook on center rack for 45 minutes.
Very good with a garden salad on a hot summer day.

title: easy breakfast
directions: Pour croutons in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with browned and drained sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix eggs with 1 1/2 cups milk and dry mustard.
Pour over top of cheese.
Cover with foil.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Mix soup with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over egg mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Allow to set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: creamy sausage stew
directions: Place potatoes in a 5-quart roasting pan.
Add onions, peppers and sausage.
Toss gently.
Combine oil, basil, salt and pepper. Pour over the meat and vegetables.
Toss well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir.
Add the cream.
Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Stir into stew.
Place on stove top, bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: darren's easy pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients together one at a time.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Dee-licious.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients, except blueberries.
Pour batter into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle blueberries on top; bake at 350° until brown.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Drain the hominy.
Melt cheese in soup.
Pour over hominy and cook in casserole dish until bubbly.
Crumble Fritos on top.

title: oven onion potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cube.
Mix oil and soup mix in a plastic bag and shake potatoes to coat.
Spread on jelly roll pan. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: quail pie
directions: Simmer quail in saucepan until tender enough to remove from bone.
Mix cornstarch with the broth that the quail was cooked in. Bring to boil, then simmer until broth thickens.
Stir often. Add meat.
Pour entire mixture into Pyrex dish.
Top with unbaked biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until biscuits are brown.
Do not overcook.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Cook soup, milk and cheese on low heat.
Add soup mixture and tuna to macaroni.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese, orange juice, and powdered sugar.
Fold in marshmallow creme.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown ground beef over medium heat and drain.
Season meat with noodles and set aside.
Mix water, vegetables, the other package of noodles (broken up), ginger and remaining seasoning in skillet. Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and let simmer for 3 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Add beef with the vegetable skillet.
Stir in green onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook on low in crock-pot for 12 hours with lid on.
Take lid off, add cinnamon, allspice and ground cloves.
Cook 3 hours with lid off.
This can be canned in pint jars or served with warm toast or muffins.
M-M-M good and you should smell it while it is cooking.

title: linguini pomodoro
directions: In a 10 to 12-inch saucepan, melt butter and olive oil over medium heat for one minute.
Add garlic and simmer for one more minute.
Add tomatoes and basil to pan and sauce for four minutes. Add chicken broth and simmer for four minutes until sauce thickens.
Add your linguini, toss and serve on platter.
Will feed four people.
Romano cheese over top, optional.

title: pickled asparagus
directions: Bring to boil water, vinegar and salt.
Boil 15 minutes. Remove all cloves from pickling spice; wrap remaining spice in cheesecloth or tea holder and hang in vinegar mixture.
Trim asparagus and blanch for 1 1/2 minutes.
Then plunge into ice water.
Place in each jar 1 clove garlic and 1 hot chili.
Pack asparagus in wide-mouth jar standing on end.
Then pour hot brine into jars.
Seal jars and store 2 or 3 months before opening.

title: banana pudding(low calorie)
directions: Mix the pudding with the milk. Add the cream cheese. Fold in the Cool Whip. Place vanilla wafers in bottom of large glass oblong dish. Add cut up bananas.
Pour filling over and top with vanilla wafers.

title: grandma's creamed coconut pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add egg yolks, milk and butter. Cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust and top with meringue.

title: 4 can soup
directions: Heat and boil 3 minutes.

title: pecan-caramel cream squares
directions: Put caramels, marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler. Place over boiling water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture is melted and smooth, about 25 minutes. Remove from heat and cool. Stir in pecans. Whip the cream and fold into caramel mixture. Combine crumbs and butter. Reserve 1/4 cup. Press remainder into bottom of 10 x 6-inch dish. Top with caramel mixture. Sprinkle with crumbs. Chill several hours or overnight. Cut into squares. Serves 6.

title: rice casserole
directions: To the 2 cups cooked rice, add the 6 remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Put orange marmalade on top. Put in oven and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: carrot rice
directions: Saute onion and carrots in pan or skillet until soft.
Add rice and mix.
Add water and bouillon; bring to a boil.
Cover and let simmer 15 minutes.
Uncover and add almonds and sugar.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, oranges, apple and celery. Add sugar. Let set. Mix Jell-O with boiling water; add fruit. Chill in fridge.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice very thin.
Sprinkle with salt and stir.
Let stand approximately 15 minutes.
Peel and slice onion (thin).
Squeeze salt water from cucumbers.
Mix other ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Add pepper.
Chill before serving.

title: broccoli casserole no. 1
directions: Boil broccoli in 1/4 cup water until tender; drain.
Place in casserole.
Mix milk, soup, onion and cheese.
Pour over broccoli. Mix cracker crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs, salt and syrup.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cranberry fruit mold
directions: Grind the cranberries.
Mix the ground cranberries and sugar until the sugar is dissolved.
Add the crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Dissolve the jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add to cranberry mix and pour into mold or large bowl.

title: ma's rolls
directions: In large bowl, stir yeast, sugar and salt.
Add shortening, warm water and flour.
Stir, then let rise for 2 hours in warm place.
After they rise double, place on floured surface, knead, then make into rolls.
Put into pans.
Let rise double again, about 2 hours.
Place in oven at 400° until brown.
Yield: 30 rolls.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 9 x 13 casserole. Melt 1 stick margarine with 1 stack crushed Ritz crackers.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: With an electric mixer, combine water, salt, butter, milk, potato flakes, cream cheese, sour cream, onion, egg, parsley and dried chives. Mix well.
Fold in Cheddar cheese.
Turn mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until heated through and bubbly.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Heat soup and enchilada sauce together.

title: springtime rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add onion and mushrooms. Cook until onion is clear.
Add rice, chicken broth and dill weed. Bring to a boil.
Turn heat to simmer. Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add asparagus.
Simmer until most liquid is absorbed. Serves 4

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a buttered 9-inch baking dish.
Combine water and cinnamon;
pour
over
apples.
Mix sugar, flour and margarine until crumbly.
Spread
over
apples.
Bake
at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve topped with ice cream if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: diet french toast strata
directions: Spray 8 x 8-inch square pan with nonstick spray. Blend 1/3 cup Splenda, egg substitute, milk, vanilla and maple extract in medium bowl. Tear cinnamon raisin bread into small 1 x 2-inch pieces. Toss bread and sliced apples with egg mixture in bowl. Coat bread evenly and pour into prepared pan. Cut cream cheese into 8 chunks and place on top. Blend remaining 1 tablespoon Splenda granular and cinnamon together. Sprinkle over strata. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly brown and set in a 350° oven. Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable jello salad
directions: Mix lime jello, hot water, cold water, mayonnaise and vinegar all together.
Let cool (thicken slightly) and whip.
Finely chop cabbage, green pepper, green onions, radishes and celery.
Add to whipped jello.
Slice stuffed olives and put in bottom of jello mold.
Pour jello mixture over top and put in refrigerator.

title: snicker pie(3 fat grams per slice)
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie crusts. Freeze; when firm, cut each pie into 8 pieces.

title: apple kugel
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted margarine, vanilla and cinnamon to beaten eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Can use a 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: fresh fruit smoothie
directions: *You can substitute any fruit for the strawberries.

title: swiss potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until crispy and crumble.
Combine first 6 ingredients and cook until tender.
Add a small amount of milk to flour.
Add slowly to first mixture.
Add remaining milk; cook until thickened.
Add cheese and bacon.

title: fried drop cakes
directions: Beat egg until light; add milk, dry ingredients (mixed and sifted) and melted butter.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot deep fat (370°); fry until light brown and cooked through, which must at first be determined with a skewer or by breaking apart.
Remove with skimmer and drain on brown paper.
Makes 12 to 15 cakes.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar, flour, baking soda, eggs, vanilla, salt and oats together and put 2/3 of mix in large jelly roll pan. Leave a 1-inch space at edge of pan as mixture will expand during baking.
Melt chips and add milk, nuts and vanilla.
Pour over cookie mixture in jelly roll pan.
Dot reserved cookie mixture by teaspoon over chocolate mixture, about 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break apart angel food cake; spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place sliced strawberries over cake.
Prepare jello using "quick set" directions on box.
Pour jello over cake and strawberries.
Cool until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar and water until it threads (240°).
Pour over egg whites and beat.
Let it stand.
Boil sugar, water and white syrup.
Cook this until it threads (248°).
Pour second mixture into first mixture and beat until quite stiff.
Add vanilla and continue beating until stiff enough to hold shape.
Add nuts, mix and drop.
Makes 5 dozen pieces.

title: tea cakes
directions: In large bowl combine first 5 ingredients; blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients; blend well.
Chill dough for easier handling.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/3 at a time on floured surface to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut with floured cookie cutter. Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
If you want to, sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until edges turn light brown.
Immediately remove.
Makes 60 to 72 cookies.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. In another bowl, combine eggs, yogurt, butter and vanilla; mix. Add to dry ingredients until just moistened. Fold in strawberries. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes until toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan. Makes 1 dozen.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of greased baking dish; lay pieces of fryer on rice and sprinkle with soup mix.
Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper; pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/4 hours; cover with foil for first part.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut apples in wedges to dip. Store in refrigerator.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs. Place in a casserole. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: apricot cookies
directions: Cut margarine in flour; mix like pie dough.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll 1 part on floured wax paper; put on cookie sheet.
Spread with apricot preserves.
Roll out other part and cut out in strips.
Lay strips 1 way, then the other.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly, then sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: big mac sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Keep in covered dish in refrigerator.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Add peaches to 2 cups water.
Cook until peaches are tender. Add sugar and stir to dissolve sugar.
Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Dip peaches out of juice and put in pan.
Add cornstarch and water to juice.
Cook until it begins to thicken. Pour over peaches and add butter.

title: zucchini mushroom casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole and top with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: bessie mae fruit salad
directions: Pour pineapple juice in pan and mix flour, sugar and marshmallows.
Cook until it begins to thicken; set aside to cool.

title: margaret washkowiak's polish pecan cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Form into walnut sized balls.
Roll in granulated sugar, place on greased cookie sheet and flatten with a glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Place pecan half on top.
Bake at 350° until light brown. When warm, not hot, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: turkey or chicken a la king
directions: In large skillet, brown onions and celery in margarine.
Add flour and mix until smooth, then add broth, milk, salt, pepper, paprika and soup.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Add pimentos, eggs, peas and chicken.
Simmer until mixture is thick, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour into toasted cups or over regular toast.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box. Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip. Crush 1/3 of Oreo cookies in 9 x 13 glass pan, then 1/3 pudding and Cool Whip and then layer. Refrigerate.

title: lemon jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add lemonade and let set in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Mix Cool Whip with a blender and pour into a 2-quart mixing bowl.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Roll out.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: helen's baked beans
directions: Mix soup, sugar, mustard and salt.
Add 2 cans of water to this and stir.
Pour over beans.
Quarter an onion and place in the corners.
Cover the top with strips of bacon.
Bake at 250° for 4 to 5 hours.
Bake, uncovered, usually 4 hours is perfect.

title: plum cobbler
directions: Sprinkle brown sugar over bottom of 10-inch pie plate. Arrange plums over sugar in baking dish.
Stir together flour, granulated sugar and cinnamon in medium size bowl.
Stir in egg until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle over plums.
Pour melted butter over top.
Place dish on aluminum foil lined baking sheet. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly. Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, syrup, salt and vanilla, then fold in oats.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, rind, and milk.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
While loaf is still hot, spread on the following mixture:
Juice of 1 lemon and 1/2 cup of sugar.

title: pudding fruit salad
directions: Prepare fruit and combine in large bowl.
In separate bowl, whisk dry pudding mix with 3/4 cup reserved pineapple juice or orange juice.
Add this sauce to fruit and gently toss to coat. It may seem a little thick but will thin while standing.
Serve or refrigerate until chilled.

title: chocolate skillet pie
directions: Sift flour, sugar and cocoa together.
Melt butter in skillet. Sift together dry ingredients and add to butter.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Stir until thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, pudding, oil, water and eggs together.
Put into a baking pan and bake at 350° until done.
Cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in butter until tender. Cook chicken in water.
Cut up chicken and add to onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook a little more and add cream of chicken soup, bouillon cubes, salt and pepper.
Mix with spaghetti.

title: kahlua
directions: Cook first three ingredients to a boil and then simmer for two hours.
Cool.
When cool add vanilla and liquor.
Best when sits for 2-4 weeks.

title: relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions in blender.
Cover ground peppers and onion in boiling water mixed with salt.
Let stand 5 minutes. Drain water.
Add sugar and vinegar to cover vegetables and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pack in jars while hot and seal.

title: leftsa (a norwegian bread)
directions: Knead together; roll out paper thin.
Brown in dry skillet. Makes 3 dozen (8 inches in diameter).

title: cake, italian cream
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and shortening. Add egg yolks. Beat well. Add soda to buttermilk, then add alternately with flour and salt mixture. Add vanilla. Fold in beaten egg whites, then gently stir in nuts and coconut. Bake in 3 (9-inch) greased and floured pans at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Melt margarine in a casserole dish.
Add rice to two cups of boiling water and set aside.
Beat egg slightly; stir in sugar, vanilla, milk and raisins and add rice.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Mix together egg yolks, oil, salt, Parmesan cheese, oregano, parsley, pepper and garlic powder. Thaw bread, but do not let rise.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan over low heat, melt 1 cup chips with margarine; remove from heat.
Add biscuit mix, sweetened condensed milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining 1 cup of chips.
Turn into well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Cut into bars.
Store in covered container.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: corn and shrimp casserole
directions: Saute pepper, celery and onion in bacon drippings.
Add corn, pimento and mushrooms.
Mix cornstarch and water and add to mixture to thicken.
Add shrimp.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in greased casserole and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: shirley's punch
directions: Mix the first five ingredients.
Make ahead and freeze. Partially thaw.
Add ginger ale and sherbet before serving. Makes 2 gallons.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Sauce:
Mix butter and 1 teaspoon of water.
Add flour.
Don't brown.
Add milk at room temperature.
Stir.
Cut cheese and add to mixture with Digol.

title: peach sweet pickles
directions: Cook until peaches are tender.
Put in jars and seal.

title: dot neal's pound cake
directions: Measure flours before sifting.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and eggs, 1 at a time, slowly to mixture.
Add a tablespoon of water to mix until ingredients are light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Flour and grease tube pan and line pan with paper, if you like, that is cut to fit the bottom.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Test with a toothpick.

title: potato and cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, celery, carrots, onion, parsley, chicken stock and pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, or until tender.
Gradually add milk and flour together until blended well.
Pour milk mixture into vegetables and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Makes 5 cups.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine the gelatin, cornstarch and sugar.
Add boiling water. Mix, return to heat and bring to boil; set aside to cool.
When cool, pour over freshly capped strawberries which have been placed in a baked pie shell.
Chill until well set.
Top with whipped cream.

title: beef wellington
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add broccoli, cheese, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spread crescent rolls out.
Spoon meat mixture onto rolls.
Roll up.
Brush with egg and bake at 375° until rolls are brown.

title: chicken onion bake
directions: Mix soup mix, dressing and water in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Roll chicken pieces in mixture.
Bake uncovered, skin side up ( or use skinned chicken), at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and water in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on racks.
Frost with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: spareribs and cabbage(culsurta)
directions: Brown onion and spareribs.
Add 1/2 cup water and cook 1`0 minutes.
Add cut up cabbage and enough water to cover cabbage. Cook 1/2 hour; add tomato paste.
Cook all together for 45 minutes to 1 hour on top of stove.

title: chicken apricot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and chill.
Serve on crisp greens.

title: banana pineapple salad
directions: Combine milk, lemon juice, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping and chill in refrigerator.
Just before serving, fold in banana slices.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in a small saucepan; stir in milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla, stirring until butter melts.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: golden parmesan cheese potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Moisten potatoes in water.
Shake potatoes in flour mixture and place in single layer in baking dish.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour.
Turn after 30 minutes with spatula.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with white or colored sugar. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss salad greens, spinach, eggs, onion, mushrooms, bean sprouts and bacon in a large bowl.
Combine oil, vinegar, chili sauce, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Pour over salad before serving.

title: great punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. When ready to serve, put in punch bowl and add lumps of sherbet.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Melt cheese and soup in small saucepan; beat until smooth.
Stir in gelatin.
Add remaining ingredients except crackers.
Mold in fish mold or small bowl. Cover and chill at least 6 hours, or until set.
Unmold; serve with crackers.
Serves 8.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, baking soda and salt. In a separate bowl, using fork or wire whisk, mix egg whites, water and corn syrup. Add to flour mixture.
Stir until smooth. Pour into prepared pan (9-inch square or 6-cup muffin tin).
Bake in a
350° oven 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
If desired, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: raisin brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter and chocolate together. Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Spread batter in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cut into 18 squares while still warm.

title: mock stuffed cabbage
directions: Prepare your own meatball recipe.
In large pot, add chili sauce, tomato sauce, cranberry and sugar.
Blend until soft.
Add meatballs.
Cook until meatballs are firm.
Stir gently. Cut cabbage into strips.
Place cabbage and sauerkraut on top.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls on a baking sheet (do not pull apart). Brush with egg whites and bake at 350° until done.

title: carrot and zucchini bars
directions: In large bowl, mix together first 5 ingredients.
In another bowl, mix rest of ingredients, except carrots.
When well blended, add carrots, then combine to flour mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on rack. Frost with Citrus Cream Cheese Frosting.
Cut into bars.

title: seafood rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Season to taste. Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves; garnish with tomato wedges. Serves 6 or 2 or 3 hungry men.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a 1 1/2 to 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add enough milk to make moist, then stir in egg yolks. Add remaining milk, vanilla and butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick like pudding.
Pour in baked deep dish pie crust.
When cool, top with egg white topping or Cool Whip. "Enjoy."

title: cheddar-macaroni salad
directions: In a large pot of boiling water, add salt and cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Cool to room temperature.
Toss with cheese, celery, green pepper and onion.

title: ham-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Finely chop mushrooms and onion. Saute in butter until tender but not browned.
Add ham, bread crumbs and pimento. Stir until combined.
Place mushroom mixture in baking dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in small saucepan over low heat.
Add cocoa, stir until blended.
Remove from heat.

title: bacon-cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then roll in chopped bacon and chill.

title: sausage and  corn cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix according to package directions.
Brown sausage and drain.
Add drained sausage to cornbread mixture.
Add soup; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking pan sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Bake until done in a 350° oven.

title: bacon canapes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix mayo, cheese and bacon together; spread on bread.
Put in oven for 4 minutes, until bubbly and hot. Spread may be made ahead and kept on bottom shelf of refrigerator.
Bacon must be very crisp.

title: holiday egg rolls
directions: Heat vegetable oil.
Cook pork until it loses color.
Add shrimp.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add vegetables and salt.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring often.
Sprinkle with cornstarch; mix well. Stir in soy sauce.
Turn into colander; cool completely.

title: easy turkey pot pie(preparation time: 16 minutes. bake time: 30 minutes.)
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Stir vegetables, turkey and soup in ungreased 9-inch pie plate. Stir remaining ingredients until blended. Pour into pie plate. Bake about 30 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients
and mix well. Chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin-peanut butter pie
directions: Add skim milk to instant vanilla pudding.
Beat with electric beater.
Stir in small can of pumpkin and peanut butter.
Pour into chocolate pie crust.
Chill.

title: symphony chicken
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in butter about 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes. Add paprika until deep red.
Lay chicken on top and cover.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour on medium heat.
Remove chicken and add sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Garnish with parsley and serve with rice.

title: lo-cal fettuccine alfredo
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Cook 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Should get more thick and bubbly.)
Stir in cream cheese; cook 2 minutes (will get very thick at this point.)
Add 1/2 to 1 cup Parmesan cheese (depending on taste), stirring constantly until it melts. Pour over hot fettuccine; toss well to coat.
Top with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper.
Serving size:
1 cup (345 calories per serving; 25% from fat).

title: baked apricots
directions: Use greased baking dish.
Put layer of peeled apricot halves, cover with brown sugar, then a layer of crumbled Ritz crackers and dot thickly with lumps of butter.
Repeat to top of dish.
Bake in 300° oven 1 hour.
Should be thick and crusty on top.
It is best to drain apricots.
Serves 10 to 12 .

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In a saucepan, combine margarine, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Immediately pour over popped pop corn.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven, spread on wax paper and break apart the large pieces.

title: the best chocolate frosting in the world
directions: Combine sugar and cream in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil gently for 6 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat.
Add chocolate; stir to blend.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Chill again, if necessary.
Makes enough to frost an 8 or 9-inch two-layer cake.

title: cream cheese and eggs
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Spread on muffins (halves). Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water.
Stir and add frozen strawberries.
Cool and chill.
When partially set, add bananas and Cool Whip.

title: roasted pecan cake
directions: Roast pecans; place shelled pecans on cookie sheet.
Put 5 to 8 pats of oleo on pieces.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring often. Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans. Use 3 (8-inch) round pans.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Quickly stir in water and drop by teaspoonful into hot oil or shortening.
Fry until golden brown. If desired, make into patties.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Put chocolate and butter into a medium heavy-bottomed saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat just until chocolate melts. Remove pan from heat and alternately stir in sugar and milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Add vanilla or liqueur.
Refrigerate, covered, up to 3 weeks.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: chicken, broccoli and sun-dried tomatoes with pasta
directions: Saute garlic and chicken in olive oil.
Add broccoli, tomatoes, seasonings, butter, wine and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer until broccoli is cooked (10 to 15 minutes).
Add cooked bow ties; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 2.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Put fruit on crust first; then pour the first mixture over fruit.
Chill for 4 to 5 hours.

title: chicken and egg noodles(easy and delicious)
directions: Mix soups together with water.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Pour soups over.
Sprinkle Lipton onion soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Boil egg noodles.
Serve chicken over egg noodles.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Mix as you would a fruit cake.
Add more flour if needed. Bake in 3 layers at 325° for 45 minutes.
Use caramel icing.

title: butternut bars
directions: Mix together the eggs, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add melted butter, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer the first 6 ingredients.
Sprinkle the sugar over the mayonnaise.
(Can put another layer of lettuce after sugar, if you want.)
Sprinkle bacon bits on top; you may also add chopped shrimp or eggs, if you wish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: pineapple jello dessert
directions: Bring Jell-O and pineapple to boil in pot on stove.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup cold water.
Mix thoroughly and put into refrigerator and let Jell-O come to a soft jell.
Then remove from fridge and beat in one container of Cool Whip and pour into dish and top with cherries and nuts and refrigerate.

title: curried chicken and broccoli
directions: Skin and debone cooked chicken breasts.
Place broccoli in buttered casserole dish and top with chicken meat.
Combine undiluted chicken soup with mayonnaise, milk, cheese, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli mixture. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Beat butter in a large bowl until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla and orange peel.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each addition.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda in small bowl.
Add to butter mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean.
Spoon Citrus Topping over hot cake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: ice cream pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, brown sugar, pumpkin pie spice and salt. Stir in softened ice cream. Pour mixture into graham cracker pie crust. Cover and put into freezer. Top with whipped cream and pecans, if desired.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and broccoli.
Cut off flowerets and place in a large bowl.
(Save stem pieces for soup.)
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain off fat!
Crumble with your hands into vegetables. Add raisins.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over salad.
Chill.
Stir before serving.

title: mint cake
