directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Add 1/4 teaspoon mint extract to batter. Beat well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool completely.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake until all are coated.
Empty in baking pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until brown.
Garnish if desired with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, milk, eggs, corn, cheese, oil, chopped onion and chopped peppers in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Put a small amount of oil in a large skillet and then pour mixture into the skillet and cook in oven on 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: In a blender, at low speed,

combine whiskey, sweetened condensed milk, eggs, vanilla, coconut and chocolate extracts, and powdered instant Espresso or coffee, until thoroughly mixed. Transfer to a bottle with a tight cover. Refrigerate overnight, or longer.
Shake well before using.
Serve cold.
Yields about 3 c.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; mash banana in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir together with a fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or less.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and whipping cream alternately.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool completely.

title: french-style bread
directions: Combine the yeast with sugar and warm water in a large bowl and allow to proof.

Mix the salt with the flour and add to the yeast mixture, a cup at a time, until you have a stiff dough. Remove to a lightly floured board and knead until no longer sticky, about 10 minutes, adding flour as necessary.
Place in a buttered bowl and turn to coat the surface with butter.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: egg white pralines
directions: Beat egg white.
Add brown sugar, vanilla, salt and pecans. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes in oven at 250°.

title: lorene's pinto chili beans
directions: Cook pinto beans slow, keeping whole.
Do not stir too much. Set aside.
Cook hamburger.
Set aside.
Cook onions.
Combine tomato sauce, soup mix, chili powder, Texas Pete, salt, sugar, pepper and hamburger.
Cook on low heat.
Pour off bean water all but 1 cup and save to use if the mixture is too dry.
Pour all of the other ingredients into the bean pot and stir easy.
Cook on low for 1/2 hour.
This makes enough for at least 8 people.
My husband says it's the best he ever ate.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a Bundt cake pan with Pam cooking spray. Mix all above ingredients and pour into pan. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. When toothpick inserted in middle of cake comes out clean, cake is done. Let cool for 2 minutes. Dump cake on a cake platter and slowly pour topping all over cake, letting topping soak in. Let cool, then serve.

title: special k bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter and stir until melted.
Stir in cereal and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together in double boiler or microwave and spread over base.

title: crispy salsa potato skins
directions: Pierce potatoes with a fork.
Microwave on high for 15 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.
Cool.
Cut each in half, then cut in half again.
Scoop out insides of potatoes, leaving 1/4 inch shell.
Preheat oven to 500 degrees.
Place potato skins, skin side down, on a foil lined broiler pan.
Brush potatoes inside and out with melted butter.
Bake potatoes until crisp and brown, about 12 minutes.
Preheat broiler.
Mix tomatoes with green chiles and onions.
Set aside.
Sprinkle potatoes with cheeses.
Broil until cheese is bubbly.
Divide salsa among potatoes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Melt butter in nonstick pan. Add flour. Stir and cook until paste forms.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Mix well.
Let mixture bubble, then stir in milk. Add vanilla. Stir and cook until desired thickness is reached.

title: freezing corn
directions: Cut off raw corn. Put corn, water, sugar and salt in large pot and cook for 5 minutes. Then put in large bowl to cool and then put in freezer bags. Place in your freezer.

title: texas brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and sugar.
In a saucepan, combine butter, shortening, coffee and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well with wooden spoon or high speed on mixer.
Pour into a well buttered 17 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cover with warm frosting.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Let grated cheese get to room temperature.
Add sausage and mix together.
When soft, work into Bisquick.
Add a dash of garlic salt and a little red pepper for a spicier flavor, if desired.
Roll mixture into balls and place in baking pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven that has been preheated.
May be made ahead and frozen.
Reheat long enough to heat through just before serving.
Makes about 100 teaspoon size balls.

title: simple bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into 1-inch pieces, enough to fill a square baking pan.
Mix ingredients and pour on bread.
Poke until all bread is soggy.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 25 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool before slicing.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Stir in margarine and sugar. Stir until well coated.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven. Stir every 8 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Pour 3 tablespoons oil in skillet and spread to cover completely.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour into skillet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Serves 8.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Brown meat, green pepper and onion together.
Season.
Add corn and jalapeno peppers to meat mixture.

title: go to meeting stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart casserole that has a tight lid.
Put lid on and cook in a 275° oven for 5 hours. Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, syrup, flavor and melted butter in a large bowl.
Add eggs; mix until all ingredients are well blended.
Stir in pecan halves.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 45 minutes or until the top of a knife inserted in the center of the pie is removed clean.

title: quick turkey a la king
directions: Saute onions and pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in gravy, soup and seasonings; add turkey and simmer 10 minutes. Serve on toast, boiled rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: leftover beef casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter for 5 minutes in microwave.
Add pot roast.
Cover with mushroom soup and water.
Microwave 10 minutes, covered.
Add chow mein noodles.
Cook uncovered for 2 minutes.

title: top of stove skillet supper
directions: Melt margarine in a large, deep heavy skillet.
Layer the next 6 ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 30 minutes. Pour beaten eggs over all. Cover and cook 15 minutes more.
Top with shredded cheese and cover for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: oh boy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a bowl, mix well.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease well.
Mix with other ingredients in crock pot until cheese is melted.
Serve with frito scoops.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into about 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet, not touching.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Use a fork to mix flour and melted margarine until crumbly. Add nuts and press in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° until brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese (softened at room temperature) and sugar until smooth.
Add 1/2 container Cool Whip; mix together and pour over crust after it's cool.
Whip pudding and milk until smooth; spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over third layer and sprinkle with nuts or slivers of chocolate, if desired.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil and 1 egg until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press the rest into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
In a separate bowl, beat softened cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg.
When crumb mixture is done, spread cream cheese mixture over the top.
Mix 1/3 cup of sugar with reserved crumb mixture.
Sprinkle on top of cream cheese and bake 12 minutes more.
Let cool, then chill before cutting.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour.
In another bowl, beat egg yolks with fork; add milk and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients into milk mixture and cook over medium heat until it boils.
Let boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, pour 1/3 pudding mixture and make a layer.
Add 1/3 bananas and 1/3 wafers. Repeat 2 more layers.
Spread with meringue over top and bake at 325° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; cool and cube.
Mix remaining ingredients with mixer and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and crumble crackers on top.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: hostess cakes
directions: Bake yellow cake according to box directions.
Let cool. Spread pudding mix (after preparing pudding according to box directions) on cake.
Spread pineapple over the pudding.
Slice bananas over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top.
Let stand for 2 hours before serving.

title: squash delight
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Separate frozen dough pieces and place in well buttered Bundt pan.
Combine dry ingredients, pudding mix, sugar and pecans. Pour melted butter over dough.
Sprinkle with dry mixture.
Leave cake pan out overnight covered with a towel.
Dough rises by morning.

title: colcannon(irish potatoes)
directions: Gently fry onion and cabbage in butter until soft.
Add milk to well mashed (no milk was added at the point of the mashing) potatoes.
Heat and beat until mixture is fluffy.
Can also be baked in a shallow pan to crisp top of potatoes.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Sift together in large bowl the first five ingredients.
Add next three ingredients and mix well.
Stir in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Turn into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan, turn onto rack to cool completely.

title: gran's corn ooh-la-la
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft.
Blend in flour and salt. Add sour cream and stir lightly, but thoroughly until smooth.
Let boil slightly and add drained corn.
Heat through.
Tastes great!

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, cracker crumbs, onion, egg, milk and salt. Shape into balls.
Brown meatballs in greased skillet.
Remove, drain and keep warm.

title: borscht (beet soup)
directions: Place neck bones in pot with enough water to cover.
Parboil, peel and grate beets into strips.
Add some salt to taste and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Add vinegar to sour cream and mix.
Add a few tablespoons to pot and keep stirring, then add hot liquid to mixture until thinned, then add to pot.
Cube 5 pounds potatoes. Add and cook until done.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Cook and stir onion and green pepper in margarine until onion is tender.
Add clams, cheese, catsup and Worcestershire sauce. Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.

title: flying quail chicken breasts
directions: Mix honey and mustard.
Baste chicken with sauce.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Turn when top surface begins to brown; baste.
Turn over at least once more and baste.

title: salmon and spinach stuffed portabellos
directions: Brush mushrooms with oil, salt and pepper.
Broil them upside down for 3 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle with tablespoon of scallions and chopped salmon on each mushroom.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well.
Blot out most of water and chop it coarsely.
Put 1 cup of spinach with cream cheese into microwave, just to melt cheese.
Mix it well with fork.
Add salt and pepper.
Layer spinach over the salmon and bake stuffed mushrooms for 20 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Process bananas with 1 can of orange juice in blender (or mash thoroughly).
Mix with remaining ingredients in plastic or glass container.
Freeze 24 hours.
Before serving, break up so that mix will be "slushy."
Add Sprite just before serving.
Serves 60.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Mix everything except shrimp with blender; spoon in the shrimp. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese on top and put in a quiche dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green chilies, cheese and onion bread
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and salt.
Stir until butter melts. Let cool to 105° to 115°.
Dissolve yeast in water in a large mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Add milk mixture and egg, stirring until well combined.
Stir in 3 cups flour.
Add enough of remaining flour to make stiff dough.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and mix with cocoa.
Cool mixture.
Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and salt.
Add vanilla.
Beat until light. Stir in chocolate, then flour.
Beat batter until smooth.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasoning.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Boil, debone and cut the fryer into bite-size pieces.
In a bowl mix the next 5 ingredients well.
Add chicken and stir well. Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Crush 1 stack of Ritz crackers and put on top of casserole.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until brown.
Freezes well!

title: vegetable pizzas
directions: Press crescent rolls into jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise and dill.
Spread on baked crust.
Sprinkle with chopped vegetables and press down a bit. Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.
Serve and enjoy!
(Best when made one day ahead.)

title: hot pepper mix for canning
directions: In each quart jar place 5 whole cloves.
Bring mixture to boil.
Pour over prepared peppers in jar.
Process at
10 pounds pressure for 25 minutes.

title: healthy candy
directions: Knead together the first 8 ingredients, adding enough honey to make a kneading consistency.
Pack into an oiled glass pie dish and press chopped nuts over the top.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Boil Veg-All and liquid for 5 minutes; drain.
Add 1/2 stick margarine and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well.
Put in Pyrex dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine; add crushed Ritz crackers.
Stir well.
Spread on top of Veg-All.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time until well mixed.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: rotel chicken casserole
directions: It is better to precook the bell pepper and onion to keep cheese from burning.
Boil chicken until chicken is done.
Take chicken out and put aside to cool.
Boil spaghetti noodles in chicken broth until done.
Drain noodles and place them in bottom of casserole dish.
Place cut up chicken, onions and bell pepper on top of noodles.
Place slices of Velveeta cheese over all. Cook slowly (covered with foil).
Casserole is done when onions and bell pepper are cooked and cheese is melted.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Melt oleo in electric skillet.
Place chicken in skillet and pour Pepsi and ketchup over chicken.
Cook at 205° for 2 hours.

title: mocha-nut butterballs
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, cream butter with sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook the lasagna noodles and drain well.
Brown ground chuck and add salt and pepper and Italian spices to taste.
When meat is browned, add spaghetti sauce and heat thoroughly.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, begin layering.
Start with noodles, then meat mixture and 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese.
Begin another layer of noodles, meat mixture and whole container of Ricotta cheese.
Begin last layer of noodles, meat mixture and top with remaining 3 cups of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with cake mix and 1 egg until doughy.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pancake omelet
directions: Melt butter in round 8-inch pan in oven while it is preheating.
Combine other ingredients and beat well with a mixer. Pour into pan with melted butter.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with syrup.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients throughly.
Chill.
May serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: lemon ambrosia
directions: Whip cream until stiff and sweeten with powdered sugar.
Line the sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers split in half.
Stand them up on end.
Cover the bottom of the pan with ladyfingers, also.

title: green chili dip
directions: Mix and let set overnight.
Great with tortilla chips.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands; form into 1 inch balls.
Roll in chocolate sprinkles and refrigerate.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; set mushrooms aside.
Chop and saute stems with minced green onion and minced green pepper.
Cook bacon; lay on Scott towel.
Drain, then crumble.
Mix mushroom stems, green onions, green pepper and the crumbled bacon together, then add the cream cheese.
Stuff mushrooms with the above mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except for crumbs and butter.
Pour into well buttered dish.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together and set aside.
Mix 2 tablespoons butter, brown sugar, walnuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla and set aside.
Cream remaining stick of butter and white sugar until light and fluffy.
Mix eggs, sour cream, bananas and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Blend into butter/sugar mixture. Blend in flour until just mixed.
Pour batter into bottom of well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and top batter with nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
(Bread is done if inserted toothpick comes out clean.)
Cool 10 minutes before turning out of pan.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and bake cake following directions on cake mix box.
Cool the layers. Drain pineapple, saving the juice. Spoon a small amount of juice evenly on each layer before spreading on the frosting. Sprinkle the pineapple over the frosting.
Continue the same procedure for each layer.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain fruit thoroughly.
Do not use juice.
Add marshmallows and coconut to fruit.
Mix sour cream into mixture.
Refrigerate for 10 to 12 hours before serving.

title: no bake hamburger cookies
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil, uncover and boil 3 minutes. then add the next 3 ingredients. Stir until all is well mixed.
Drop by tsp. onto wax paper. After they set place on a nilla wafer.
Add a drop of yellow and a drop of red frosting (either buy colored frosting or mix food coloring with vanilla icing) for the ketchup and mustard.
Place a nilla wafer on top.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour measure and return to sifter, add soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening and add sugar gradually, creaming it in as it is added.
Add eggs one at a time beating each one in as it is added.
Now stir in the molasses.
Add dry ingredients gradually until batter is smooth.
Cover dough with wax paper and chill, 1 hour.
Grease cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Take a teaspoon of dough and roll into ball, size of walnut and roll in sugar. Put on cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine the all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour and baking soda;

set aside. In the large bowl of an electric mixer, beat the margarine, granulated sugar and brown sugar at moderately low speed for 2 minutes or until smooth and creamy, then beat in the egg, egg white and vanilla extract.

Using a wooden spoon, mix in the dry ingredients and grated chocolate. Drop the dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets, spacing the cookies about 2-inches apart. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned around the edges.
Remove immediately to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 36 cookies.
One cookie:
45 calories, 2 g fat (saturated fat 0 g) and 15 mg sodium.

title: no cook fudge cookie
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Quickly add the oats, salt and vanilla. Drop by spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool completely.

title: crab cakes
directions: Clean crabmeat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into cakes (the size you prefer).
Cook until golden brown on outside.

title: deviled ham cheese ball
directions: Blend Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and deviled ham with a mixer on low speed.
Refrigerate for a while so mixture can be handled.
Turn out mixture onto a surface and shape into a ball. Roll ball into chopped nuts, coating the surface.
Keep cheese ball chilled until 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Combine dressing mix with crackers.
Stir in dill weed.
Add oil.
It will seem oily at first, but it will be fine.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all together; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam).
Refrigerate overnight.
Place into cold oven; bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until set.

title: pumpernickel bread dip
directions: Cut top off bread and scoop out the inside of bread, break it in pieces.
Mix sour cream, shrimp and dressing together; put in center of hollowed out bread and dip bread pieces in it.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and crackers thoroughly and pour into baking dish.
Melt one stick butter and mix with 1 sleeve of ritz crackers (crushed).
Put on top of other ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Put cut-up chicken and onion into water and cook slowly until tender.
Add salt.
Remove chicken and cut meat into small pieces. Return to broth, together with corn, celery and carrots. Continue to simmer.
Add eggs last 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: cheddar biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a medium bowl, combine first six ingredients.
Using a fork, cut butter into mixture until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; stir in cheese and buttermilk.

title: full of baloney
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange potatoes, bologna, green pepper, flour and seasoning in layers in 1 1/2-quart baking dish, dotting each layer with butter.
Pour milk over and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars and vanilla. Mix really well. Mix in eggs and peanut butter. Slowly add flour and baking soda. Until all flour is absorbed. Batter will be thick.
Take teaspoon full and roll into a ball. Place on greased cookie sheet. Using a fork press cookie ball flat. (making a pattern in cookie). Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 min. Enjoy!

title: mustard-dill sauce for smoked salmon
directions: Whisk first 5 ingredients in medium bowl to blend. Stir in dill. Season sauce to taste with salt and pepper.
Can be prepared 2 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 6 servings.

title: oven french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place potatoes, that have been peeled and cut into French fry-style slices, on lightly greased (Pam) cookie sheet.
Brush lightly with 1/3 of oil.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Brush with oil again and bake for 5 minutes.
Brush with remaining oil and bake for 5 more minutes, until crisp and tender. Sprinkle with salt, if desired.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, molasses, soda and vinegar.
Add sifted flour, salt and spices.
Roll thin on a pastry cloth.
Bake in moderate oven at 375°.
Watch carefully, as ginger cookies burn easily.

title: fruit 'n' juice breakfast shake
directions: Break banana into small pieces and put in the blender with pineapple juice, yogurt and strawberries.
Secure lid and blend until smooth.
Divide shake between two glasses and serve immediately.

title: scallopped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce of the first 5 ingredients.
Add cheese. Place 1/2 of the potatoes in a greased casserole (2-quart).
Cover with 1/2 of onion and 1/2 the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour.

title: jew bread
directions: Put brown sugar and eggs in double boiler and cook for twenty minutes. Pour hot water out of double boiler and add cold water, allow contents to cool. Blend in flour and vanilla. Add nuts last. Pour in ungreased pan. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grate squash and combine with onion, green pepper and parsley. Season with nutmeg, salt and pepper. Combine bacon drippings, 1 cup bread crumbs, milk and slightly beaten egg. Fold into squash mixture. Pour into greased casserole dish. Fry bacon until crisp. Crumble and combine with remaining bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german beans
directions: Saute green pepper in butter.
Mix with lima beans, tomato soup and chunked Velveeta cheese (much as desired). Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: 16 layer jello
directions: Arrange colors of the Jell-O any way you like.
With 1 cup hot water, mix with first color and stir. Separate 1/2 mixture.
With half, add 1/3 cup sour cream. Stir and pour into deep dish, 9 1/2 x 11 x 2-inches (glass is nice).
Let set up in refrigerator. When set, pour 1/2 plain mixture.
When set continue same way with all colors.

title: fruit and nut tossed salad
directions: In large bowl, combine spinach, lettuce, grapes, almonds and oranges.
In a screw top jar, combine remaining ingredients except avocado; shake well.
Just before serving, toss some of the dressing with the salad and garnish with avocado.
Serve remaining dressing on side.
Makes 8 servings.

title: best pumpkin bread
directions: Mix and pour into 3 well-greased 8 x 5-inch loaf pans or 7 small loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chili mac
directions: In large heavy pan, brown hamburger, onion and chili powder. Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: dream cookies(light, crisp and crunchy)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, beat well.
Mix dry ingredients all together.
Mix together both mixtures.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.

title: raczhal(hungarian fish dish)
directions: Slowly mix paprika and sour cream. Refrigerate.
Peel and slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick and lay in buttered Pyrex baking dish. Cut bacon in squares and put over potatoes.
Add salt and pepper. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Add layer of sliced onion, salt and pepper.
Bake 15 minutes. Add sliced tomatoes, sliced green peppers, salt and pepper.
Bake 30 minutes. Add fillets of fish, salt and pepper. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Spread paprika sauce over fish. Bake 1 to 2 minutes.

title: pepperoni lasagna
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 30 minutes.
Combine eggs, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Spread 1/2 cup meat sauce in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Layer with 4 lasagna noodles.
Add cottage cheese mixture and layer of pepperoni.
Top with remaining lasagna noodles and meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer. Let stand 15 minutes to set up before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan or deep pot.
Cook squash, carrots and onion until tender, add remaining ingredients.
Pour in baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. (Makes a lot and freezes well.)

title: poached pears with almonds
directions: Peel pears and cut out blossom end. Do not remove stems.
In deep saucepan, mix sugar, orange juice, lemon juice, lemon rind and ginger. Bring to boiling.
Place pears in syrup. Bring to boiling again. Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until pears are tender when pierced with a fork.
Arrange pears in deep serving dish. Pour syrup over top.
Sprinkle with the almonds. Serve slightly warm or chilled with whipped cream, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix butter and crumbs.
Line half in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over the crumbs and top with remaining crumbs. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: southern cracker-fried chicken
directions: Place buttermilk in a shallow dish.
Combine crackers, garlic powder, sage, salt and pepper in a plastic bag; shake to mix thoroughly.
Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk.
Place one or two pieces at a time in bag; shake to coat.
In a large, deep frying pan, melt lard over medium-high heat to 375°.
Add chicken pieces; cook, turning frequently, until brown and crispy, about 20 minutes.
Drain on paper towels before serving.
Serves 4.

title: sweet pickle peaches
directions: Select firm clingstone peaches.
Peel and drop at once into a sirup which is made by boiling together 1/2
the sugar and water, and boiling for 15 minutes.
Cool and allow to stand for 2-3 hours.
Drain off sirup, put vinegar and spices and balance of sugar into it, and cook 15 minutes.
Add peaches and cook together for 1/2 hour.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain off the sirup, cook for 20 minutes, add peaches and continue cooking for 15 minutes.
Cool again and let stand at least 2 hours or overnight, then cook all together again until peaches are clear and tender.
Pack peaches into jars, cover with strained sirup, and seal.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order. Pour into greased pan and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: diabetic - whipped summer squash
directions: Peel and cut squash into small pieces.
Place in saucepan with small amount of water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer until squash is crisp-tender.
Drain.
Beat squash with rotary beater. Add evaporated milk and butter; beat until light and fluffy.
Add salt and pepper.
Yields 4 servings.

title: gazpacho(makes 6 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for at least 2 hours.
It can be pureed, too, if you like a less "chunky" soup.

title: never fail banana bread
directions: *To sour milk:
1/2 cup milk with 1/2 tablespoon vinegar.

title: italian lentil soup
directions: In large kettle, boil lentils in water for 1/2 hour.
Add carrots, celery, oil, salt and pepper.
Continue boiling slowly for 2 to 3 hours, depending on thickness desired.
During last 1/2 hour, add tomato sauce, marjoram, rice, noodles or spaghetti.

title: pasta with sausage and peas
directions: Cook pasta as package label directs.
Meanwhile, in skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Add sausage and onions; saute 10 minutes or until browned, breaking up sausage.
Add chicken broth and peas.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until peas are tender.

title: ellie's pecan pie
directions: Mix all together real good; pour into pie shell and bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream delight
directions: Mix crackers and margarine well and press firmly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix the ice cream and pudding together; pour over cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.
Better after at least 12 hours.
You may freeze this for later.
Keeps in refrigerator for several days.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish in order listed. Cover tightly and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Combine rice-vermicelli with ground beef and beaten egg. Shape into small meatballs (about 20).
Brown on all sides in skillet.
Combine contents of flavor packet with water.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Thicken gravy if desired.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine, sugar and 1/4 cup chopped nuts like pie dough.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: baked b.b.q. pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops and put in shallow pan.
Combine brown sugar, water and catsup.
Spoon over the chops.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour, or until done.
Cover the first half of baking time.
Uncover the last half of baking time.
Turn chops once.

title: taco lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef, green pepper and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Add water and taco seasoning; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 2 minutes. Stir in the black beans and tomatoes. Simmer, uncovered for 10 minutes. Place two tortillas in a greased	13x9x2 inch baking dish. Spread with half of the refried beans and beef mixture; sprinkle with 1 c. cheese. Repeat layers. Top with remaining tortillas and cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: crystallized grapes and oranges
directions: Dip the fruit into the egg white.
Lift up the fruit using a fork or fingers.
(Don't take up too much egg, the fruit should be barely wet.)
Place 10 to 12 pieces of fruit on a cookie sheet with the sugar and shake the pan so that the fruit gets coated with sugar.
Place the pieces on a cookie sheet and let them dry, either outside or in the refrigerator.
Serve with a sprig of mint.

title: party nachos
directions: Saute chopped veggies until tender.
Add hamburger meat and mash with potato masher.
Cook until meat is done.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning and tomatoes.
Salt to taste.
Cook approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat, grate cheese for top.

title: pecan brittle
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook until it spins a thread (very hard ball stage).
Add pecans and cook until it caramelizes (turns tan).
Remove from heat and add butter.
Stir until it is blended and add soda.
When it foams up, pour onto buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: japanese persimmon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together honey, butter and oil. Beat
egg
lightly	and
add.
Prepare persimmon pulp by cutting persimmon
in
half.
Scoop out the pulp, removing any seeds, and break up the fruit with your fingertips.
Dissolve baking soda
in pulp.
Combine
persimmon with honey mixture. Stir nuts,
raisins and salt into flour.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Stir
dry ingredients
into
wet
ones.
Drop by heaping teaspoons
onto oiled cookie sheets.
Bake 20 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Spray 13 x 9 baking dish with Pam. In your skillet, add your cream cheese, green chilies and cooked chicken together. Cook on low to medium heat and stir until cream cheese has melted. Spoon chicken filling onto tortillas; roll up and place seam side down in baking dish. Pour enchilada sauce over top; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and cheese has melted. Should make 6 to 10 enchiladas.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Chop the rhubarb and place in an unbaked pie shell.
Pour on top of rhubarb the first four ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Test by making a soft ball in water.
Boil about 6 1/2 minutes on medium heat.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix in desired seasonings.
Spread into 9 to 10-inch pie plate.
Cover with pizza sauce.
Spread onion and green pepper over sauce.
Layer pepperoni evenly over top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over pepperoni and bake until cheese is melted (about 5 minutes).
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: matt's dry rub
directions: Combine spices and rub 2/3 on the fat side of brisket and 1/3 on bottom side before grilling.

title: greek shrimp fondue(serves 4)
directions: Heat olive oil in a fondue pot.
Add onions and garlic and saute until onions soften.
Add tomato puree, white wine, oregano and red pepper flakes.
Keep fondue pot at simmer.
Add Feta cheese and cook until melted.
Add parsley, salt and pepper. Serve hot, dipping seafood and small potatoes.

title: banana cream cake
directions: Mix pudding mix, milk and powdered sugar and stir in 2 1/2 cups banana.
Slice cake into 3 layers.
Place 1 layer on bottom, then spread 1 1/2 cups filling between each layer and on top. Spread Cool Whip on top and garnish with bananas and coconut.

title: romanian paklava
directions: Mix finely chopped nuts with sugar.
Slowly melt butter and margarine together and allow to slowly boil over low heat for 5 minutes.
Do not stir.
Lay out first layer of filo; spread about 3 teaspoons butter on it.
Sprinkle with nuts and sugar.
Do the same with second and third layers.
Roll lengthwise on dowel or stick. Squeeze ends together and remove stick.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until slightly browned (about 15 minutes).
When cool, cut on diagonal and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: kim chee
directions: Wash cabbage.
Cut in 1 1/2 x 2-inch slices.
Dissolve salt in water.
Soak cabbage in brine 8 hours or overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine seasonings.
Add to cabbage and mix thoroughly. Pack in 1 quart jar.
Cover loosely and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Tighten cover and refrigerate for 3 days to ripen before serving.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: sausage cheese grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 3-quart baking dish.
Bring water to boil.
Stir in grits.
Reduce heat; cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and butter until melted. Add eggs, milk and sausage; blend well.
Pour into prepared dish; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: carol's frozen salad
directions: Blend cheese and sugar.
Add juice and sour cream.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and freeze.
Thaw 2 hours before serving.

title: fettuccine with vodka and tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion.
Saute until tender.
Stir in garlic and saute 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, vodka and red pepper. Simmer, stirring to break up tomatoes, until sauce is reduced and thickened (15 minutes).
Stir in cream and simmer.
Stir until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Season with salt.
Add cooked pasta and parsley.
